1
00:00:00,227 --> 00:00:02,097
(The members are taken somewhere in a boat.)

2
00:00:02,767 --> 00:00:04,497
(That's not a house!)

3
00:00:05,237 --> 00:00:07,637
(The base camp is a deserted island.)

4
00:00:07,907 --> 00:00:10,776
(The deserted island check-in mission begins.)

5
00:00:10,777 --> 00:00:11,876
Stand up!

6
00:00:11,877 --> 00:00:14,447
(Yong Jin is left on the deserted island.)

7
00:00:14,707 --> 00:00:17,177
(There's really nothing here.)

8
00:00:17,647 --> 00:00:21,387
(He must survive somehow.)

9
00:00:22,317 --> 00:00:25,757
(The other members enjoy a trek.)

10
00:00:26,327 --> 00:00:28,457
(It's paradise compared to the deserted island.)

11
00:00:28,987 --> 00:00:32,897
(But the deserted island check-in continues.)

12
00:00:33,967 --> 00:00:36,197
(Se Yoon gets deserted.)

13
00:00:36,897 --> 00:00:39,466
(The torment is too much for him...)

14
00:00:39,467 --> 00:00:41,367
(when there's nothing to eat.)

15
00:00:41,907 --> 00:00:45,177
(While the deserted suffer, )

16
00:00:45,937 --> 00:00:49,977
(the others play a catch a tail check-in mission.)

17
00:00:50,247 --> 00:00:51,947
(Jong Min ends up on the island.)

18
00:00:53,247 --> 00:00:56,917
(2 Days 1 Night)

19
00:00:56,987 --> 00:00:58,056
I'm on board.

20
00:00:58,057 --> 00:01:01,087
(Jong Min heads to the deserted island.)

21
00:01:01,457 --> 00:01:04,997
Lee Joon and that mouse.

22
00:01:05,327 --> 00:01:08,066
The mouse and its tail move as one.

23
00:01:08,067 --> 00:01:09,296
(DinDin and Joon move as one.)

24
00:01:09,297 --> 00:01:11,237
Ki Taek is mouse poop.

25
00:01:11,597 --> 00:01:13,036
Why mouse poop?

26
00:01:13,037 --> 00:01:14,207
He'll get dumped soon.

27
00:01:14,967 --> 00:01:16,837
He's inside the mouse right now.

28
00:01:17,077 --> 00:01:19,007
One fight and they'll ditch him.

29
00:01:19,847 --> 00:01:21,407
Ki Taek, you chose wrong.

30
00:01:22,047 --> 00:01:24,977
My two large younger brothers are on the island.

31
00:01:25,517 --> 00:01:26,787
I can rely on them.

32
00:01:27,147 --> 00:01:28,687
I'll lead them to get revenge.

33
00:01:29,287 --> 00:01:31,387
Life is all about revenge.

34
00:01:32,117 --> 00:01:34,157
That's one reason you live.

35
00:01:35,057 --> 00:01:36,356
The island is within view.

36
00:01:36,357 --> 00:01:38,517
(Discussing revenge brought him closer to the island.)

37
00:01:41,097 --> 00:01:42,097
(Why is he sitting like this?)

38
00:01:42,098 --> 00:01:44,067
- Explain the pose.
- They don't know I'm coming.

39
00:01:45,137 --> 00:01:47,767
(Hiding for a dramatic reunion)

40
00:01:48,537 --> 00:01:50,577
- I don't see anyone.
- They went somewhere?

41
00:01:51,477 --> 00:01:52,677
There's no one there.

42
00:01:53,507 --> 00:01:55,276
Yong Jin. I can't do this.

43
00:01:55,277 --> 00:01:57,947
I must have a peanut candy.

44
00:01:59,517 --> 00:02:01,446
- Peanut candy...
- It's open.

45
00:02:01,447 --> 00:02:03,357
- Do you want one?
- Sounds good.

46
00:02:03,557 --> 00:02:04,557
Yes, then...

47
00:02:04,558 --> 00:02:08,427
(They earned the candy with all their might.)

48
00:02:09,327 --> 00:02:10,556
(They eat their hard-earned sustenance.)

49
00:02:10,557 --> 00:02:11,557
That's it.

50
00:02:12,227 --> 00:02:13,767
Can I swap this with a snack?

51
00:02:14,297 --> 00:02:15,326
This isn't easy.

52
00:02:15,327 --> 00:02:16,337
(Rummaging)

53
00:02:17,967 --> 00:02:19,467
Didn't I get two candies?

54
00:02:19,867 --> 00:02:21,467
You got just one.

55
00:02:22,207 --> 00:02:24,977
- Why?
- You won one round and got one.

56
00:02:25,277 --> 00:02:26,646
- And I gave it to him?
- Yes.

57
00:02:26,647 --> 00:02:28,477
(I gave him the only one I had?)

58
00:02:29,077 --> 00:02:30,777
(Chews it quickly)

59
00:02:31,347 --> 00:02:32,376
(What a mistake to make.)

60
00:02:32,377 --> 00:02:33,387
Darn it.

61
00:02:34,047 --> 00:02:35,316
(Makes an extra loud noise chewing)

62
00:02:35,317 --> 00:02:37,387
- I have good teeth.
- I miscalculated.

63
00:02:37,917 --> 00:02:41,026
(Feeling lost)

64
00:02:41,027 --> 00:02:43,226
I like how the flavor spreads in my mouth.

65
00:02:43,227 --> 00:02:46,096
(The candy tastes extra sweet on the deserted island.)

66
00:02:46,097 --> 00:02:47,897
- Wait. There's a boat.
- Or... Is it here?

67
00:02:48,327 --> 00:02:49,596
It's coming toward us.

68
00:02:49,597 --> 00:02:51,673
- Should we go and welcome them?
- Se Yoon. They're really coming.

69
00:02:51,697 --> 00:02:52,697
My gosh.

70
00:02:52,698 --> 00:02:54,636
It's really coming toward us.

71
00:02:54,637 --> 00:02:56,106
(They happily rush out to welcome the boat.)

72
00:02:56,107 --> 00:02:57,437
Who do you think it is?

73
00:02:57,837 --> 00:02:58,837
Ki Taek.

74
00:02:59,437 --> 00:03:00,607
I'm getting a feeling that...

75
00:03:01,347 --> 00:03:02,646
it might be DinDin.

76
00:03:02,647 --> 00:03:04,293
- Someone is on the boat.
- It's DinDin's voice.

77
00:03:04,317 --> 00:03:05,976
- Someone's on it.
- I must have super hearing.

78
00:03:05,977 --> 00:03:07,147
I just heard DinDin's voice.

79
00:03:07,587 --> 00:03:09,246
- Who is it?
- Why is he coming here?

80
00:03:09,247 --> 00:03:10,457
I think it's Jong Min.

81
00:03:11,187 --> 00:03:12,287
It's Jong Min.

82
00:03:12,987 --> 00:03:14,156
Jong Min is here.

83
00:03:14,157 --> 00:03:15,656
(Peekaboo)

84
00:03:15,657 --> 00:03:17,017
Darn. Another useless guy is here.

85
00:03:17,497 --> 00:03:18,726
All the old members are here.

86
00:03:18,727 --> 00:03:20,497
They sent only the oldies to the island.

87
00:03:21,467 --> 00:03:22,866
(Crawling out in an entertaining manner)

88
00:03:22,867 --> 00:03:23,867
Jong Min.

89
00:03:24,567 --> 00:03:25,796
(It's me.)

90
00:03:25,797 --> 00:03:26,867
Hurry up!

91
00:03:27,567 --> 00:03:28,867
Hurry up, mister!

92
00:03:29,637 --> 00:03:32,637
Gosh, those younger ones teamed up and ganged up on me.

93
00:03:32,837 --> 00:03:34,047
- They got rid of you?
- Yes.

94
00:03:34,277 --> 00:03:36,346
I told you. Now, we have a mouse, a mouse's tail,

95
00:03:36,347 --> 00:03:37,516
and a mouse dropping.

96
00:03:37,517 --> 00:03:38,646
There's a long mouse dropping?

97
00:03:38,647 --> 00:03:40,417
Yes. There's a long one. It's Ki Taek.

98
00:03:40,787 --> 00:03:43,816
(The Mouse Tails have been assembled now.)

99
00:03:43,817 --> 00:03:45,556
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

100
00:03:45,557 --> 00:03:46,857
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

101
00:03:47,457 --> 00:03:48,887
2 Days 1 Night during summer...

102
00:03:50,097 --> 00:03:53,366
This is nice. I'd love to go breezy and take a nap.

103
00:03:53,367 --> 00:03:54,466
(Cooling down the heat with a cold drink)

104
00:03:54,467 --> 00:03:55,666
It's already 4pm.

105
00:03:55,667 --> 00:03:57,643
This is the first time I haven't done anything exhausting.

106
00:03:57,667 --> 00:03:58,796
What are you talking about?

107
00:03:58,797 --> 00:04:00,483
- We played a lot of games.
- This is nothing.

108
00:04:00,507 --> 00:04:01,866
I feel bad that...

109
00:04:01,867 --> 00:04:03,236
I'm getting paid for this today.

110
00:04:03,237 --> 00:04:04,807
- Then don't get paid.
- Right.

111
00:04:04,977 --> 00:04:06,106
Don't pay Joon.

112
00:04:06,107 --> 00:04:07,877
- Save the money for team dinners.
- It's...

113
00:04:08,107 --> 00:04:09,547
Let's save that up for team dinners.

114
00:04:09,647 --> 00:04:11,946
Since we're on the subject, should we have it tomorrow?

115
00:04:11,947 --> 00:04:13,547
Okay. You're good.

116
00:04:14,687 --> 00:04:15,746
He's good.

117
00:04:15,747 --> 00:04:17,756
Because you have a low-pitched voice,

118
00:04:17,757 --> 00:04:18,987
you sounded very genuine.

119
00:04:19,557 --> 00:04:20,856
- I meant it.
- You have a pleasant voice.

120
00:04:20,857 --> 00:04:22,857
- Really?
- Because you meant it.

121
00:04:24,457 --> 00:04:28,366
(They're taking a nap for complete relaxation.)

122
00:04:28,367 --> 00:04:29,467
He's got something for us.

123
00:04:29,767 --> 00:04:31,743
- The third member to check in is...
- What's going on?

124
00:04:31,767 --> 00:04:34,067
- Jong Min. Welcome.
- Yes. Do I get a benefit?

125
00:04:34,267 --> 00:04:36,036
- I'll give you a welcome kit.
- I see.

126
00:04:36,037 --> 00:04:37,437
- What?
- Here you go.

127
00:04:38,737 --> 00:04:39,776
- What?
- What?

128
00:04:39,777 --> 00:04:41,076
(It's different from the ones we got.)

129
00:04:41,077 --> 00:04:42,077
What about us?

130
00:04:42,078 --> 00:04:43,376
Jong Min, we have to use them together.

131
00:04:43,377 --> 00:04:44,676
You could be in big trouble if you act like that here.

132
00:04:44,677 --> 00:04:46,146
- Jong Min, you'll get in trouble.
- Jong Min.

133
00:04:46,147 --> 00:04:47,986
- We're in this together.
- This could be bad for you.

134
00:04:47,987 --> 00:04:49,563
- Wait.
- As for the envelope I gave you,

135
00:04:49,587 --> 00:04:51,986
open it when things get tough.

136
00:04:51,987 --> 00:04:53,267
- Okay.
- We should open it now.

137
00:04:53,927 --> 00:04:54,927
(Jong Min tucks it in his back pocket right away.)

138
00:04:54,928 --> 00:04:56,496
- What about us?
- You can open it whenever you want.

139
00:04:56,497 --> 00:04:58,226
You can discuss it among yourselves.

140
00:04:58,227 --> 00:04:59,643
- This is getting really tough.
- Let's open it now.

141
00:04:59,667 --> 00:05:01,296
Hey. What did you guys do here?

142
00:05:01,297 --> 00:05:02,496
You guys look perfectly fine.

143
00:05:02,497 --> 00:05:04,736
Do you know how many hours I've been here?

144
00:05:04,737 --> 00:05:06,867
- How many hours?
- It's been four hours.

145
00:05:07,737 --> 00:05:09,607
- Jong Min. It's been seven for me.
- Yes?

146
00:05:10,107 --> 00:05:11,876
- Jong Min.
- What did you do here?

147
00:05:11,877 --> 00:05:13,776
It's been seven hours for me. Let's open it up.

148
00:05:13,777 --> 00:05:15,446
Can one of us take a peek?

149
00:05:15,447 --> 00:05:18,016
- Is it over once we open it?
- Yes, it's over then.

150
00:05:18,017 --> 00:05:19,216
Let's open it when things get unbearable.

151
00:05:19,217 --> 00:05:20,347
- No.
- Let's open it now.

152
00:05:20,847 --> 00:05:24,217
We really need more stuff. We should open it.

153
00:05:24,587 --> 00:05:25,857
Already?

154
00:05:26,117 --> 00:05:27,256
Let's open it when it gets unbearable.

155
00:05:27,257 --> 00:05:29,217
- We're opening it too soon.
- Come on, Jong Min.

156
00:05:29,327 --> 00:05:30,356
That's enough, Jong Min.

157
00:05:30,357 --> 00:05:32,133
(The man who's been here for 7 hours explodes.)

158
00:05:32,157 --> 00:05:33,496
- My gosh.
- I've been here for seven hours.

159
00:05:33,497 --> 00:05:34,773
Come on. Let's see what's in there.

160
00:05:34,797 --> 00:05:35,966
His eyes went wild. Did you see that?

161
00:05:35,967 --> 00:05:37,367
I'll pretend I didn't see that.

162
00:05:37,537 --> 00:05:38,766
Please let's open it, Jong Min.

163
00:05:38,767 --> 00:05:39,836
You could go crazy...

164
00:05:39,837 --> 00:05:40,906
- on deserted islands.
- Jong Min.

165
00:05:40,907 --> 00:05:42,507
- Should I open it now?
- Let's open it.

166
00:05:42,767 --> 00:05:44,077
- Can I open it now?
- Yes.

167
00:05:44,337 --> 00:05:46,337
Well, I can handle this for now.

168
00:05:46,977 --> 00:05:49,057
- Don't say that.
- But I'm doing it for their sake.

169
00:05:49,477 --> 00:05:50,916
Jong Min. Think about it.

170
00:05:50,917 --> 00:05:52,676
You came here because the younger ones abandoned you.

171
00:05:52,677 --> 00:05:54,046
- Right.
- Then we're in this together.

172
00:05:54,047 --> 00:05:55,886
- Only we show you respect.
- The mouse, the mouse's tail,

173
00:05:55,887 --> 00:05:57,057
and the mouse dropping.

174
00:05:57,787 --> 00:05:59,257
What do you want? Like desserts?

175
00:05:59,557 --> 00:06:00,627
Like red bean bingsu.

176
00:06:00,957 --> 00:06:02,387
One, two, three.

177
00:06:03,627 --> 00:06:05,697
"The last chance to turn the tables around."

178
00:06:05,957 --> 00:06:07,966
"Get to the inhabited island right now..."

179
00:06:07,967 --> 00:06:09,287
"and switch the island location."

180
00:06:09,737 --> 00:06:12,067
- What does this mean?
- I guess we can switch places!

181
00:06:12,297 --> 00:06:13,667
- We can make them pay.
- What?

182
00:06:14,167 --> 00:06:15,237
- That must be it.
- What?

183
00:06:15,367 --> 00:06:16,607
Look. It's 3 against 3.

184
00:06:16,907 --> 00:06:17,907
If we win,

185
00:06:17,908 --> 00:06:19,337
- we can switch places.
- Right.

186
00:06:20,207 --> 00:06:21,776
- We have to leave?
- Right now.

187
00:06:21,777 --> 00:06:23,253
- I just got here.
- You want us to leave?

188
00:06:23,277 --> 00:06:25,077
Then you should have told me to stay there.

189
00:06:25,377 --> 00:06:26,586
- Look, Jong Min.
- What?

190
00:06:26,587 --> 00:06:27,916
What if we opened it when things got unbearable?

191
00:06:27,917 --> 00:06:30,117
What if we opened it around 7pm or 8pm?

192
00:06:30,557 --> 00:06:31,816
- Right.
- See? Please.

193
00:06:31,817 --> 00:06:33,287
You should have trusted me sooner.

194
00:06:33,587 --> 00:06:35,156
- I'm glad we opened it.
- Yes. It was the right call.

195
00:06:35,157 --> 00:06:36,287
See?

196
00:06:36,627 --> 00:06:38,496
- Let's go and catch the mice.
- Let's catch the mice.

197
00:06:38,497 --> 00:06:41,196
(Team OB is on their way to catch the mice.)

198
00:06:41,197 --> 00:06:43,636
Everyone, let's continue the trip.

199
00:06:43,637 --> 00:06:44,637
- Sounds good.
- Okay.

200
00:06:45,367 --> 00:06:46,566
We got to take a break...

201
00:06:46,567 --> 00:06:48,306
(They're in a good mood after a nice break.)

202
00:06:48,307 --> 00:06:49,937
- here and there.
- Seriously.

203
00:06:50,377 --> 00:06:51,477
It's nice.

204
00:06:51,907 --> 00:06:53,476
- Taking a break is helpful.
- We need to rest.

205
00:06:53,477 --> 00:06:54,477
Yes.

206
00:06:54,478 --> 00:06:55,977
This is lovely.

207
00:06:56,277 --> 00:06:57,446
When we face them again,

208
00:06:57,447 --> 00:06:59,447
we must be ready to handle the criticism.

209
00:06:59,577 --> 00:07:00,947
- Gosh, what's going on?
- What?

210
00:07:02,517 --> 00:07:04,086
(There's a mudflat in front of them.)

211
00:07:04,087 --> 00:07:05,156
- What's going on?
- Hey, what's this?

212
00:07:05,157 --> 00:07:06,626
I guess we're going into the mudflat.

213
00:07:06,627 --> 00:07:08,656
Filming on the mudflats ranks among the top three...

214
00:07:08,657 --> 00:07:10,126
- What's this?
- grueling shoots.

215
00:07:10,127 --> 00:07:11,197
Come on. What is this?

216
00:07:12,057 --> 00:07:13,927
What's going on? That's the mudflat.

217
00:07:14,727 --> 00:07:15,996
This is my first time.

218
00:07:15,997 --> 00:07:17,836
- That's the mudflat.
- It has to be my first time.

219
00:07:17,837 --> 00:07:18,837
Nothing is set up here.

220
00:07:18,838 --> 00:07:20,566
Are we going to race on the mudflat to get flags?

221
00:07:20,567 --> 00:07:22,767
It looks like we'll have to compete against each other.

222
00:07:24,007 --> 00:07:26,376
(They head to the battlefield after getting changed.)

223
00:07:26,377 --> 00:07:27,623
Hey, I have a bad feeling about this.

224
00:07:27,647 --> 00:07:29,007
Wait. Where do we need to go?

225
00:07:29,207 --> 00:07:32,246
So taking this route here is the easiest.

226
00:07:32,247 --> 00:07:33,747
(Ki Taek is stuck from the get-go.)

227
00:07:34,317 --> 00:07:37,457
(He tries to make his way one step at a time.)

228
00:07:38,187 --> 00:07:39,357
(Staggering)

229
00:07:39,587 --> 00:07:40,686
(Ki Taek is struggling.)

230
00:07:40,687 --> 00:07:42,827
(Cheol is breezing through.)

231
00:07:43,227 --> 00:07:46,157
(Filming on the mudflat isn't easy for the variety show rookie.)

232
00:07:46,457 --> 00:07:47,627
- By the way, - Yes.

233
00:07:47,927 --> 00:07:48,997
It's cool here.

234
00:07:49,167 --> 00:07:50,196
You're super positive.

235
00:07:50,197 --> 00:07:51,296
- It's cool.
- That's great.

236
00:07:51,297 --> 00:07:52,737
It feels good once you give up.

237
00:07:53,097 --> 00:07:54,166
- It's cool here.
- Yes.

238
00:07:54,167 --> 00:07:55,706
It gets easier on the mudflat once you give up.

239
00:07:55,707 --> 00:07:57,677
- This is nice. I'm...
- Yes.

240
00:07:57,837 --> 00:07:58,876
In a good mood.

241
00:07:58,877 --> 00:08:01,147
Gosh. You rude jerks.

242
00:08:04,847 --> 00:08:06,076
We're back.

243
00:08:06,077 --> 00:08:07,587
My gosh. They're back.

244
00:08:08,447 --> 00:08:10,016
I thought Yong Jin changed his residence to the island.

245
00:08:10,017 --> 00:08:11,186
He's like a guest.

246
00:08:11,187 --> 00:08:12,357
(Team OB is full of spite.)

247
00:08:13,457 --> 00:08:14,727
Hello.

248
00:08:14,887 --> 00:08:16,357
It's over for you guys.

249
00:08:17,357 --> 00:08:18,657
I brought them here.

250
00:08:19,927 --> 00:08:21,327
Why do you look down?

251
00:08:21,767 --> 00:08:23,737
What's the problem? Say something.

252
00:08:24,037 --> 00:08:26,237
I brought Zhang Fei and Zhuge Liang.

253
00:08:26,837 --> 00:08:28,966
We're here to catch the mouse, the mouse's tail, and the dropping.

254
00:08:28,967 --> 00:08:30,207
- My goodness.
- Hey.

255
00:08:31,337 --> 00:08:33,253
(He was walking over to them, acting all high and mighty.)

256
00:08:33,277 --> 00:08:35,377
(Sinking in)

257
00:08:35,547 --> 00:08:36,977
- You don't look okay.
- My gosh.

258
00:08:37,147 --> 00:08:38,877
- And you think you can catch us?
- You...

259
00:08:39,077 --> 00:08:40,647
How will you catch us if you're stuck?

260
00:08:40,787 --> 00:08:42,587
- Is this normal?
- You punks.

261
00:08:42,687 --> 00:08:44,817
I brought the nutria to catch you mice.

262
00:08:44,957 --> 00:08:46,186
- Welcome.
- How am I going to get there?

263
00:08:46,187 --> 00:08:47,826
Wait, this is harder than I thought.

264
00:08:47,827 --> 00:08:48,957
- Gosh.
- I can't do this.

265
00:08:49,527 --> 00:08:50,656
This is the worst one yet.

266
00:08:50,657 --> 00:08:52,137
(This match is going to work, right?)

267
00:08:52,197 --> 00:08:53,867
- Guys.
- We're here for revenge.

268
00:08:54,167 --> 00:08:55,227
Guys.

269
00:08:55,797 --> 00:08:57,036
- By the way, Yong Jin...
- Any hunches?

270
00:08:57,037 --> 00:08:59,497
Yong Jin might have forgotten how to speak.

271
00:09:00,237 --> 00:09:01,766
- Are you okay?
- He stayed there for too long.

272
00:09:01,767 --> 00:09:03,553
I escaped the island after spending eight hours there.

273
00:09:03,577 --> 00:09:04,936
Tell us what you've been up to.

274
00:09:04,937 --> 00:09:06,277
I came here after eight hours.

275
00:09:06,437 --> 00:09:07,846
I don't know.

276
00:09:07,847 --> 00:09:09,576
It wasn't physically taxing or anything.

277
00:09:09,577 --> 00:09:11,276
This variety show is all about the bond among the members.

278
00:09:11,277 --> 00:09:12,677
But there were no members.

279
00:09:13,447 --> 00:09:16,386
Their absence definitely drove me to loneliness.

280
00:09:16,387 --> 00:09:17,387
- Right.
- Yes.

281
00:09:17,587 --> 00:09:18,787
Guys.

282
00:09:19,487 --> 00:09:22,186
We're going to begin Switch the Islands Mission...

283
00:09:22,187 --> 00:09:23,456
- now.
- What?

284
00:09:23,457 --> 00:09:24,796
- Switch?
- Yes.

285
00:09:24,797 --> 00:09:26,357
- If we win this game, - That too.

286
00:09:26,897 --> 00:09:28,266
They'll go back to the island?

287
00:09:28,267 --> 00:09:30,097
Did you hear that? This is what he does!

288
00:09:30,637 --> 00:09:31,973
- That little mouse.
- What do we do?

289
00:09:31,997 --> 00:09:33,836
- But...
- You know what?

290
00:09:33,837 --> 00:09:36,067
- I'm impressed by DinDin.
- Why do you say that?

291
00:09:36,207 --> 00:09:37,376
- Typically, people would think...
- Yes.

292
00:09:37,377 --> 00:09:38,806
"Wait. If we lose, we'll go to the deserted island."

293
00:09:38,807 --> 00:09:40,007
That's what most people think.

294
00:09:40,107 --> 00:09:42,507
But you said, "They'll go back to the island?"

295
00:09:42,807 --> 00:09:44,246
- No, it's not like that.
- Gosh, this jerk.

296
00:09:44,247 --> 00:09:46,246
- I feel bad now.
- That's what he assumed right away.

297
00:09:46,247 --> 00:09:48,416
- It's not that. Losing...
- By default, you don't think...

298
00:09:48,417 --> 00:09:49,846
you'll end up there.

299
00:09:49,847 --> 00:09:51,916
I rarely think that I'm going to lose to them.

300
00:09:51,917 --> 00:09:53,086
Gosh, look at this punk.

301
00:09:53,087 --> 00:09:55,686
- Look at your team.
- Nutria, let's catch the mouse.

302
00:09:55,687 --> 00:09:56,726
Look at your team.

303
00:09:56,727 --> 00:09:58,226
One of them can't even get up.

304
00:09:58,227 --> 00:10:00,166
Yong Jin, there are cockles here.

305
00:10:00,167 --> 00:10:02,496
Let's cook them on the island later. Let's gather some.

306
00:10:02,497 --> 00:10:03,936
One of them can't even get up.

307
00:10:03,937 --> 00:10:05,473
- Yong Jin, we can't win this game.
- But...

308
00:10:05,497 --> 00:10:08,207
You really need to give it your all.

309
00:10:08,867 --> 00:10:10,777
- Dinner is at stake too.
- Oh, my.

310
00:10:10,837 --> 00:10:12,737
- I feel so bad now.
- That's a huge benefit.

311
00:10:12,937 --> 00:10:15,177
- I feel so bad. Oh, no.
- A meal is on the line.

312
00:10:15,507 --> 00:10:17,777
The winning team will get a filling meal...

313
00:10:18,117 --> 00:10:20,346
with fresh conger eels from Wando.

314
00:10:20,347 --> 00:10:21,547
- Conger eels?
- Conger eels.

315
00:10:21,617 --> 00:10:23,317
- They're nice and plump.
- Conger eels!

316
00:10:23,517 --> 00:10:25,057
Conger eels!

317
00:10:26,417 --> 00:10:27,856
- The losing team...
- Cup noodles?

318
00:10:27,857 --> 00:10:29,657
Will go to the deserted island immediately...

319
00:10:30,297 --> 00:10:32,126
- and get a boxed meal.
- A boxed meal?

320
00:10:32,127 --> 00:10:33,196
- Yes.
- You'll give us boxed meals?

321
00:10:33,197 --> 00:10:34,367
- That's a relief.
- No way!

322
00:10:34,997 --> 00:10:36,366
I really wanted to eat boxed eels.

323
00:10:36,367 --> 00:10:38,867
Come on, guys! We must aim to eat the conger eels!

324
00:10:40,507 --> 00:10:42,607
- What about cup noodles?
- You're driving me crazy.

325
00:10:42,767 --> 00:10:45,006
- We need some soup.
- What soup?

326
00:10:45,007 --> 00:10:47,076
- Yong Jin, there are cockles here.
- You must aim to win!

327
00:10:47,077 --> 00:10:48,706
Come on. We have to eat the conger eels.

328
00:10:48,707 --> 00:10:51,053
- My gosh. You're frustrating.
- Give me a basket for the cockles.

329
00:10:51,077 --> 00:10:52,476
They have no motivation to fight.

330
00:10:52,477 --> 00:10:54,716
- Boxed meals are pretty good.
- Seriously.

331
00:10:54,717 --> 00:10:56,986
- How come you're not aiming to win?
- They gave up the moment...

332
00:10:56,987 --> 00:10:58,087
they set foot here.

333
00:10:58,417 --> 00:11:01,387
All right. This mission will be a 3-on-3 game.

334
00:11:02,187 --> 00:11:04,556
- It's Mudflat Touchdown.
- Touchdown?

335
00:11:04,557 --> 00:11:05,926
- What's that?
- We're playing American football.

336
00:11:05,927 --> 00:11:07,566
- Yes. You must carry the ball...
- Like rugby.

337
00:11:07,567 --> 00:11:09,166
Into your opponent's end zone for a touchdown...

338
00:11:09,167 --> 00:11:10,497
to score.

339
00:11:10,937 --> 00:11:14,166
However, you can't throw the ball to reach the end zone.

340
00:11:14,167 --> 00:11:15,736
You will not earn a point that way.

341
00:11:15,737 --> 00:11:16,776
- We have to carry the ball.
- So keep that in mind.

342
00:11:16,777 --> 00:11:18,406
- We must carry it.
- You can throw your body...

343
00:11:18,407 --> 00:11:20,176
for the touchdown.

344
00:11:20,177 --> 00:11:21,276
We have to get it past the line?

345
00:11:21,277 --> 00:11:24,217
The team that scores three points will win the mission.

346
00:11:24,817 --> 00:11:26,216
(Team YB starts warming up right away.)

347
00:11:26,217 --> 00:11:28,986
- Look.
- It's working.

348
00:11:28,987 --> 00:11:31,356
(Rookie Taek is having a hard time on the mudflat.)

349
00:11:31,357 --> 00:11:32,387
Hey.

350
00:11:33,757 --> 00:11:36,327
We got this! Joon got this!

351
00:11:36,857 --> 00:11:38,526
- It's better to throw it hard.
- Try getting up.

352
00:11:38,527 --> 00:11:39,827
- Yes.
- You can do this.

353
00:11:40,067 --> 00:11:41,603
- Of course, I can do this.
- You can do this.

354
00:11:41,627 --> 00:11:42,926
- Let's get a taste of those eels.
- They...

355
00:11:42,927 --> 00:11:44,937
Se Yoon can move around well.

356
00:11:45,867 --> 00:11:48,836
(Which team will end up on the deserted island?)

357
00:11:48,837 --> 00:11:50,106
- Jong Min.
- All right.

358
00:11:50,107 --> 00:11:51,506
I'll give you time to strategize.

359
00:11:51,507 --> 00:11:53,507
(Why don't you strategize?)

360
00:11:53,947 --> 00:11:55,277
We have to win this game.

361
00:11:55,707 --> 00:11:57,717
Ki Taek, don't run. Just stay here.

362
00:11:57,947 --> 00:11:59,816
- Stay here?
- Stay around here.

363
00:11:59,817 --> 00:12:01,023
(Assigning Ki Taek in the back for solid defense)

364
00:12:01,047 --> 00:12:04,356
Joon, you need to be where Jong Min is.

365
00:12:04,357 --> 00:12:06,056
- Okay.
- Yes.

366
00:12:06,057 --> 00:12:07,886
Hey, we have to get the ball into the goalpost, right?

367
00:12:07,887 --> 00:12:10,327
Yes. Bring the ball into the goalpost.

368
00:12:11,357 --> 00:12:12,603
Play as if our lives depended on it.

369
00:12:12,627 --> 00:12:14,147
- We have to.
- Let's give it our all.

370
00:12:14,627 --> 00:12:15,896
If we're going to win, we might as well make it...

371
00:12:15,897 --> 00:12:17,297
- a total shutout.
- Let's do that.

372
00:12:17,397 --> 00:12:19,136
That way, we won't feel as bad.

373
00:12:19,137 --> 00:12:20,983
(Because the alternative would make us feel bad.)

374
00:12:21,007 --> 00:12:22,266
- Just block them.
- Jong Min.

375
00:12:22,267 --> 00:12:23,976
- Are there any holes in my defense?
- No.

376
00:12:23,977 --> 00:12:25,137
No? Yes or no?

377
00:12:25,637 --> 00:12:26,777
- No.
- No.

378
00:12:27,207 --> 00:12:28,807
- They'd better not come here.
- Listen.

379
00:12:29,607 --> 00:12:32,077
Yong Jin, when we begin, you can start running with the ball.

380
00:12:32,277 --> 00:12:34,087
I'll just run without the ball.

381
00:12:34,347 --> 00:12:35,886
Throw me the ball if they catch you.

382
00:12:35,887 --> 00:12:37,816
(While Se Yoon is putting up ironclad defense...)

383
00:12:37,817 --> 00:12:39,757
I'll run in front of you and push them away.

384
00:12:40,427 --> 00:12:42,657
- You get it, right?
- Are you guys ready?

385
00:12:43,557 --> 00:12:44,697
I'm already tired.

386
00:12:45,957 --> 00:12:47,827
- I'm hungry.
- I'm also hungry.

387
00:12:48,027 --> 00:12:49,766
A hungry lion must hunt more aggressively.

388
00:12:49,767 --> 00:12:51,566
You already have a solid build.

389
00:12:51,567 --> 00:12:52,736
There's no way they can score.

390
00:12:52,737 --> 00:12:54,066
Just don't let them score.

391
00:12:54,067 --> 00:12:55,466
- Yes.
- I'll block everyone.

392
00:12:55,467 --> 00:12:57,336
Let's do this. Let's go! We got this.

393
00:12:57,337 --> 00:12:58,536
(Let's stay on the inhabited island, Team OB!)

394
00:12:58,537 --> 00:13:00,106
- Team YB must go!
- Let's go!

395
00:13:00,107 --> 00:13:01,506
- Let's go.
- Team YB!

396
00:13:01,507 --> 00:13:03,976
(Team YB must go to the deserted island.)

397
00:13:03,977 --> 00:13:06,476
I hate deserted islands! I love inhabited islands!

398
00:13:06,477 --> 00:13:07,546
Get ready.

399
00:13:07,547 --> 00:13:08,816
Just go for it.

400
00:13:08,817 --> 00:13:10,986
(Team OB versus Team YB)

401
00:13:10,987 --> 00:13:13,317
Go. Come on. What are you doing? Grab the ball.

402
00:13:13,457 --> 00:13:14,626
Slide.

403
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:16,363
(Jong Min and Yong Jin quickly penetrate into the enemy lines.)

404
00:13:16,387 --> 00:13:17,987
(Forward Joon of Team YB plows through.)

405
00:13:18,727 --> 00:13:20,367
- You got it. Over here.
- My gosh, Joon.

406
00:13:20,427 --> 00:13:21,497
Okay.

407
00:13:22,497 --> 00:13:23,737
Stay on Joon.

408
00:13:24,137 --> 00:13:25,137
- Ki Taek.
- No.

409
00:13:25,138 --> 00:13:26,496
Don't stay on Joon. It's fine.

410
00:13:26,497 --> 00:13:27,836
- Not yet.
- We got Se Yoon over there.

411
00:13:27,837 --> 00:13:29,467
- Hold onto that.
- Over there.

412
00:13:30,037 --> 00:13:31,507
- My gosh.
- No.

413
00:13:32,477 --> 00:13:33,477
- Run.
- Not yet.

414
00:13:33,478 --> 00:13:34,906
- It's okay. I got Joon.
- All right.

415
00:13:34,907 --> 00:13:36,047
- It's okay.
- Here.

416
00:13:36,477 --> 00:13:38,376
Jong Min, you can't stay there. You have to block them.

417
00:13:38,377 --> 00:13:39,377
(Jong Min)

418
00:13:39,378 --> 00:13:40,816
Jong Min, you need to block them.

419
00:13:40,817 --> 00:13:42,147
(Jong Min, get back on defense.)

420
00:13:42,787 --> 00:13:45,187
(Bulldozer Jong Min keeps moving forward.)

421
00:13:45,287 --> 00:13:46,387
I know that.

422
00:13:46,957 --> 00:13:48,386
What are you doing?

423
00:13:48,387 --> 00:13:49,726
(I want to go back, but I'm physically unable to do it.)

424
00:13:49,727 --> 00:13:51,127
- Jong Min.
- Stay close.

425
00:13:51,257 --> 00:13:52,326
I'll step out.

426
00:13:52,327 --> 00:13:53,807
(Without Jong Min, it's 2 against 1.)

427
00:13:54,827 --> 00:13:56,266
Jong Min, what are you doing? Come back here now.

428
00:13:56,267 --> 00:13:57,267
My gosh.

429
00:13:57,667 --> 00:13:59,567
- Gosh, what's this?
- I'll hold Yong Jin down.

430
00:14:00,237 --> 00:14:02,317
Okay. There's no way he can get past Se Yoon. Right.

431
00:14:03,677 --> 00:14:05,976
(Fatty Moon is guarding the gate of Team OB.)

432
00:14:05,977 --> 00:14:07,177
Get the ball!

433
00:14:08,247 --> 00:14:10,577
- Joon. Throw it to me.
- Grab it.

434
00:14:11,017 --> 00:14:12,046
- No.
- There you go.

435
00:14:12,047 --> 00:14:13,047
We got it.

436
00:14:14,417 --> 00:14:15,547
Move forward.

437
00:14:15,987 --> 00:14:17,086
Over here.

438
00:14:17,087 --> 00:14:18,087
Pass it to Jong Min.

439
00:14:18,087 --> 00:14:19,087
- Yes!
- Catch it.

440
00:14:19,088 --> 00:14:20,387
- Let's go.
- Touch it down!

441
00:14:20,787 --> 00:14:21,886
Touch it down!

442
00:14:21,887 --> 00:14:23,897
(There's no one guarding the goalpost.)

443
00:14:24,057 --> 00:14:25,197
Touch it down.

444
00:14:26,297 --> 00:14:28,127
(Let's score the opening point.)

445
00:14:28,497 --> 00:14:29,697
Ki Taek, run!

446
00:14:30,267 --> 00:14:32,097
(Mouse Dropping runs as fast as he can.)

447
00:14:32,897 --> 00:14:33,937
I got it.

448
00:14:35,067 --> 00:14:36,536
(The perfect counterattack opportunity)

449
00:14:36,537 --> 00:14:38,007
(Will Team OB score first?)

450
00:14:39,337 --> 00:14:40,346
I got it.

451
00:14:40,347 --> 00:14:42,947
(Ki Taek's super save)

452
00:14:44,317 --> 00:14:46,717
(The forward wastes the perfect chance to score.)

453
00:14:46,917 --> 00:14:48,786
How could you fail to score?

454
00:14:48,787 --> 00:14:50,887
(How could you fail to score?)

455
00:14:51,587 --> 00:14:52,587
(Sighing)

456
00:14:52,757 --> 00:14:53,857
Get the ball.

457
00:14:54,887 --> 00:14:56,026
- Ki Taek.
- To the back.

458
00:14:56,027 --> 00:14:57,557
(Flustered)

459
00:14:58,557 --> 00:14:59,857
- Joon.
- Cheol.

460
00:15:00,597 --> 00:15:01,867
Throw it back hard.

461
00:15:02,497 --> 00:15:04,067
- Hey.
- Throw it back hard.

462
00:15:04,897 --> 00:15:05,897
No.

463
00:15:07,707 --> 00:15:09,137
- I'm stuck.
- Okay.

464
00:15:10,407 --> 00:15:12,107
- Come here.
- You think you can stop me?

465
00:15:12,477 --> 00:15:13,507
Come here.

466
00:15:14,107 --> 00:15:16,577
(Brimming with confidence)

467
00:15:17,217 --> 00:15:19,417
Joon, let's strategize.

468
00:15:19,917 --> 00:15:22,487
Se Yoon, please stop them!

469
00:15:22,587 --> 00:15:24,657
And what will you do to help?

470
00:15:25,317 --> 00:15:27,126
If you pass it to me, I'll score.

471
00:15:27,127 --> 00:15:28,726
(I'm glued to the goalpost.)

472
00:15:28,727 --> 00:15:30,087
Steal the ball and throw it to me.

473
00:15:30,527 --> 00:15:33,766
(1 defender versus 2 attackers)

474
00:15:33,767 --> 00:15:36,567
All right. I'll do it. Stay in the back.

475
00:15:37,267 --> 00:15:39,467
(Fatty Moon is guarding Team OB with ironclad defense.)

476
00:15:41,807 --> 00:15:43,137
(Joon holds down Se Yoon.)

477
00:15:43,237 --> 00:15:44,877
(DinDin pushes forward behind Se Yoon.)

478
00:15:45,277 --> 00:15:46,307
No.

479
00:15:46,677 --> 00:15:47,807
- What's this?
- Go!

480
00:15:47,977 --> 00:15:49,047
No!

481
00:15:49,407 --> 00:15:50,417
Ki Taek!

482
00:15:51,447 --> 00:15:52,693
- Ki Taek, we need you.
- Ki Taek.

483
00:15:52,717 --> 00:15:54,017
(Striding)

484
00:15:54,147 --> 00:15:55,586
- Okay.
- Go.

485
00:15:55,587 --> 00:15:56,716
(With Ki Taek and Yong Jin, )

486
00:15:56,717 --> 00:15:59,287
(it's now become 2 defenders against 3 attackers.)

487
00:16:02,827 --> 00:16:03,827
My gosh.

488
00:16:06,557 --> 00:16:07,566
(A nice punch)

489
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:08,567
Ki Taek.

490
00:16:10,167 --> 00:16:11,266
What are you doing, Jong Min?

491
00:16:11,267 --> 00:16:12,436
(As Team YB catches the ball again, they continue their offense.)

492
00:16:12,437 --> 00:16:13,437
Se Yoon. There you go.

493
00:16:13,438 --> 00:16:15,007
- No.
- It's out.

494
00:16:15,507 --> 00:16:17,407
- It went out of bounds.
- It didn't go in.

495
00:16:18,277 --> 00:16:19,307
Pass it to me now!

496
00:16:20,377 --> 00:16:22,177
- Pass it to me now!
- Pass it to Jong Min.

497
00:16:22,377 --> 00:16:24,017
Guard the goalpost, Ki Taek.

498
00:16:24,347 --> 00:16:25,846
There you go. Grab it.

499
00:16:25,847 --> 00:16:26,847
My gosh.

500
00:16:27,087 --> 00:16:29,147
(The pass falls just a bit short.)

501
00:16:30,657 --> 00:16:33,157
(He quickly rushes over to stop Jong Min.)

502
00:16:33,757 --> 00:16:35,686
(Joon, Jong Min)

503
00:16:35,687 --> 00:16:37,326
(Joon quickly runs toward Jong Min...)

504
00:16:37,327 --> 00:16:39,967
(as Jong Min has the perfect chance to score without any defense.)

505
00:16:41,397 --> 00:16:43,937
(Closing the gap in the blink of an eye)

506
00:16:49,867 --> 00:16:50,876
Grab it.

507
00:16:50,877 --> 00:16:52,237
(Please stop Jong Min.)

508
00:16:53,277 --> 00:16:54,277
You got it!

509
00:16:55,198 --> 00:16:56,238
