773
00:26:33,378 --> 00:26:36,318
(Stunned by the unexpected defeat)

774
00:26:37,518 --> 00:26:43,058
(Team YB let victory slip away when they had almost won.)

775
00:26:43,688 --> 00:26:46,628
(In disbelief)

776
00:26:46,798 --> 00:26:48,428
After an intense game...

777
00:26:48,558 --> 00:26:50,328
of the mudflat touchdown,

778
00:26:50,428 --> 00:26:52,028
Team OB wins.

779
00:26:52,068 --> 00:26:54,898
(Team OB secures the inhabited island.)

780
00:26:55,338 --> 00:26:57,637
Everyone, Team YB who lost...

781
00:26:57,638 --> 00:27:01,337
will go and check in at the deserted island.

782
00:27:01,338 --> 00:27:02,538
- Okay.
- Let's get going.

783
00:27:03,508 --> 00:27:05,077
- Well done.
- Well done, everyone.

784
00:27:05,078 --> 00:27:06,078
Good job.

785
00:27:06,079 --> 00:27:07,347
- We did our best.
- It was a great game.

786
00:27:07,348 --> 00:27:09,918
Well done, Joon.

787
00:27:10,388 --> 00:27:11,987
- You too.
- Well done, DinDin.

788
00:27:11,988 --> 00:27:12,988
Wasn't it fair play?

789
00:27:12,989 --> 00:27:14,457
- Yes, it was fair play.
- Are you all right?

790
00:27:14,458 --> 00:27:16,758
- Yes, I'm good.
- No one played dirty.

791
00:27:17,628 --> 00:27:19,228
I will slate.

792
00:27:19,598 --> 00:27:21,557
- One, two, three.
- Gosh.

793
00:27:21,558 --> 00:27:22,758
Okay.

794
00:27:23,628 --> 00:27:25,798
(Covered in soil)

795
00:27:26,298 --> 00:27:29,338
(Covered in mud)

796
00:27:29,608 --> 00:27:31,538
I just wanted to slate.

797
00:27:32,808 --> 00:27:33,978
He can't even get up.

798
00:27:34,808 --> 00:27:37,577
(A large goby appears on the mudflat.)

799
00:27:37,578 --> 00:27:38,647
My feet are dirty.

800
00:27:38,648 --> 00:27:40,047
- This is on another level.
- Yes.

801
00:27:40,048 --> 00:27:42,478
It's tough on another level.

802
00:27:43,348 --> 00:27:45,448
All right. Well done, everyone.

803
00:27:45,848 --> 00:27:46,988
Let's go.

804
00:27:47,088 --> 00:27:48,887
- Can I grab this?
- Yes.

805
00:27:48,888 --> 00:27:49,958
All right.

806
00:27:50,728 --> 00:27:51,857
(The members help out.)

807
00:27:51,858 --> 00:27:53,128
One, two.

808
00:27:54,628 --> 00:27:55,958
Gosh, are you okay?

809
00:27:56,158 --> 00:27:57,428
My shoes are too big.

810
00:27:57,868 --> 00:27:59,427
Your shoes are too big?

811
00:27:59,428 --> 00:28:02,068
(A mudflat battle forged through everyone's laughter and struggle)

812
00:28:02,438 --> 00:28:06,038
(And the people who made it happen)

813
00:28:06,878 --> 00:28:10,248
(You all did an amazing job.)

814
00:28:10,608 --> 00:28:14,148
(After a match that felt like a movie)

815
00:28:15,148 --> 00:28:18,247
(The sunset painted the sky of Geumdang Island in deep red.)

816
00:28:18,248 --> 00:28:20,088
- Let's go eat.
- Thank you.

817
00:28:20,218 --> 00:28:22,018
- Let's enjoy our victory.
- Please do.

818
00:28:22,418 --> 00:28:24,818
(Team OB is still unable to snap out of the joy of victory.)

819
00:28:24,888 --> 00:28:25,957
We won.

820
00:28:25,958 --> 00:28:27,857
Don't cry. Are you crying?

821
00:28:27,858 --> 00:28:29,028
(It's too early to cry.)

822
00:28:29,668 --> 00:28:31,397
I will regain all the strength I lost.

823
00:28:31,398 --> 00:28:33,398
- We had to bet our life on it.
- Seriously.

824
00:28:34,038 --> 00:28:35,437
(Chewy conger eel)

825
00:28:35,438 --> 00:28:37,937
(A delicacy coated with spicy sauce)

826
00:28:37,938 --> 00:28:40,038
(Spicy stir-fried conger eel)

827
00:28:41,438 --> 00:28:43,707
(A generous serving of plump conger eel)

828
00:28:43,708 --> 00:28:46,077
(Conger eel stew)

829
00:28:46,078 --> 00:28:48,347
The specialty of Geumdang Island, a conger eel set meal.

830
00:28:48,348 --> 00:28:49,718
- My gosh.
- Goodness.

831
00:28:50,318 --> 00:28:52,647
- Goodness.
- This is why we do it.

832
00:28:52,648 --> 00:28:54,258
We're very touched.

833
00:28:54,958 --> 00:28:57,328
- Thank you.
- I didn't think it was possible.

834
00:28:57,588 --> 00:28:59,158
Shall we make a toast?

835
00:28:59,258 --> 00:29:00,738
- This is a proper meal.
- Thank you.

836
00:29:01,258 --> 00:29:02,357
When you say "old boy,"

837
00:29:02,358 --> 00:29:03,698
we'll say "the last dance."

838
00:29:04,468 --> 00:29:05,468
That sounds great.

839
00:29:05,728 --> 00:29:06,767
Old boy.

840
00:29:06,768 --> 00:29:07,967
- The last dance.
- Dance.

841
00:29:07,968 --> 00:29:09,098
(Old Boys forever)

842
00:29:10,668 --> 00:29:12,067
Our last dance was amazing.

843
00:29:12,068 --> 00:29:13,078
(The water is tasty.)

844
00:29:13,638 --> 00:29:14,807
One, two, three.

845
00:29:14,808 --> 00:29:16,608
(Are you watching this, YB?)

846
00:29:16,748 --> 00:29:18,207
- Thank you for the food.
- Please enjoy it.

847
00:29:18,208 --> 00:29:19,277
Thank you for the food.

848
00:29:19,278 --> 00:29:21,048
As we worked hard, it'll be much tastier.

849
00:29:21,778 --> 00:29:24,117
(It's Yong Jin's first proper meal after 10 hours.)

850
00:29:24,118 --> 00:29:25,148
Yes.

851
00:29:25,618 --> 00:29:27,988
- Goodness.
- This is real nourishment.

852
00:29:28,958 --> 00:29:30,028
Yes.

853
00:29:30,558 --> 00:29:32,558
(A flavor that makes you cheer out loud)

854
00:29:32,858 --> 00:29:35,058
It wipes away all the suffering on the deserted island.

855
00:29:35,828 --> 00:29:37,228
- With just one bite, right?
- Yes.

856
00:29:38,198 --> 00:29:39,427
- The broth is really...
- It's rich and delicious.

857
00:29:39,428 --> 00:29:40,437
Yes.

858
00:29:40,438 --> 00:29:42,268
- The food is good here.
- It's very rich.

859
00:29:42,838 --> 00:29:44,607
- It's delicious.
- Isn't it on another level?

860
00:29:44,608 --> 00:29:46,508
- Yes, it's on another level.
- It is.

861
00:29:47,038 --> 00:29:48,077
Goodness.

862
00:29:48,078 --> 00:29:49,278
(A bite of the eel tail)

863
00:29:50,148 --> 00:29:52,147
- It's nice and spicy.
- Is this spicy?

864
00:29:52,148 --> 00:29:53,218
It's very spicy.

865
00:29:54,648 --> 00:29:55,777
It melts in my mouth.

866
00:29:55,778 --> 00:29:58,178
(The conger eels' distinctive chewy texture is exceptional.)

867
00:29:58,218 --> 00:29:59,448
I should make a wrap.

868
00:29:59,818 --> 00:30:00,818
With that?

869
00:30:00,988 --> 00:30:02,988
Look at the lettuce.

870
00:30:03,658 --> 00:30:07,158
I'm 100 percent sure that it was grown here.

871
00:30:07,998 --> 00:30:09,327
You can't buy it like this.

872
00:30:09,328 --> 00:30:11,298
(Lettuce wraps become trendy following Jong Min.)

873
00:30:12,128 --> 00:30:13,767
You have to eat the entire lettuce without cutting.

874
00:30:13,768 --> 00:30:14,768
Yes.

875
00:30:14,769 --> 00:30:16,197
Cut it in half. Otherwise, it's too big.

876
00:30:16,198 --> 00:30:17,207
- No.
- No way.

877
00:30:17,208 --> 00:30:18,968
- It's as big as a plastic bag.
- No.

878
00:30:19,108 --> 00:30:20,807
Have some garlic too.

879
00:30:20,808 --> 00:30:21,907
Put a lot of this.

880
00:30:21,908 --> 00:30:23,724
(Two pieces of meat without rice on half a lettuce)

881
00:30:23,748 --> 00:30:25,248
(Is that really all?)

882
00:30:25,808 --> 00:30:28,448
(He wraps it neatly and eats it all at once.)

883
00:30:29,318 --> 00:30:31,678
(The eel's savory flavor and spiciness spread as you chew.)

884
00:30:31,948 --> 00:30:33,818
(What about the food teacher's wrap?)

885
00:30:34,118 --> 00:30:35,757
(Lettuce, rice, eel)

886
00:30:35,758 --> 00:30:37,558
- Add garlic and onion.
- He's putting a lot.

887
00:30:38,058 --> 00:30:39,128
Goodness.

888
00:30:39,388 --> 00:30:40,758
Can we get some more garlic?

889
00:30:41,158 --> 00:30:43,028
This is like Park Chan Ho's baseball.

890
00:30:44,968 --> 00:30:46,798
(He stuffed the huge bite into his mouth.)

891
00:30:47,238 --> 00:30:48,797
(Same lettuce, different size)

892
00:30:48,798 --> 00:30:50,268
(Yong Jin's wrap, Se Yoon's wrap)

893
00:30:50,538 --> 00:30:53,218
(The more you eat, the more moving the conger eel's charm becomes.)

894
00:30:53,338 --> 00:30:55,807
Is this what it tastes like to celebrate...

895
00:30:55,808 --> 00:30:57,408
after winning a crucial final match?

896
00:30:58,248 --> 00:30:59,548
- Right?
- Right.

897
00:31:00,118 --> 00:31:01,547
Sharing a moment like this...

898
00:31:01,548 --> 00:31:02,847
(They act like a winning team at the global soccer event.)

899
00:31:02,848 --> 00:31:04,418
Food is delicious when shared.

900
00:31:05,748 --> 00:31:08,287
In a life-threatening situation,

901
00:31:08,288 --> 00:31:11,128
everything seems to move in slow motion.

902
00:31:11,558 --> 00:31:13,197
While trying to steal the ball from Joon,

903
00:31:13,198 --> 00:31:15,558
I was wondering if I should give up or not.

904
00:31:16,058 --> 00:31:17,798
Then Yong Jin stole the ball.

905
00:31:17,868 --> 00:31:19,128
Suddenly,

906
00:31:19,268 --> 00:31:20,597
Yong Jin threw the ball as planned.

907
00:31:20,598 --> 00:31:21,637
He threw it towards the goal.

908
00:31:21,638 --> 00:31:22,668
That's it.

909
00:31:22,768 --> 00:31:24,268
Then he looked at me.

910
00:31:24,508 --> 00:31:26,808
"If you don't run, I'll kill you."

911
00:31:27,008 --> 00:31:28,277
I saw that look in his eyes.

912
00:31:28,278 --> 00:31:29,908
- Run.
- "Run."

913
00:31:30,478 --> 00:31:31,808
The look in his eyes...

914
00:31:33,518 --> 00:31:35,748
(His fierce glare that made Fatty Se Yoon run)

915
00:31:35,878 --> 00:31:37,648
- You saw it in slow motion?
- Exactly.

916
00:31:38,218 --> 00:31:39,717
Eat a lot, Se Yoon.

917
00:31:39,718 --> 00:31:40,817
(Help yourself. You did a good job.)

918
00:31:40,818 --> 00:31:41,957
Okay, Jong Min.

919
00:31:41,958 --> 00:31:43,058
(He's eating more himself.)

920
00:31:43,828 --> 00:31:45,028
(Glancing)

921
00:31:46,698 --> 00:31:48,727
Put a lot in it. The lettuce is big.

922
00:31:48,728 --> 00:31:49,797
Be careful, it's hot.

923
00:31:49,798 --> 00:31:51,158
(Suddenly, he makes another wrap.)

924
00:31:52,028 --> 00:31:54,498
(He's approaching the camera.)

925
00:31:55,498 --> 00:31:57,637
You worked very hard. He spent...

926
00:31:57,638 --> 00:31:59,507
eight hours with me on the deserted island.

927
00:31:59,508 --> 00:32:01,148
- He was with you for eight hours?
- Yes.

928
00:32:01,738 --> 00:32:03,107
I wonder what they're eating.

929
00:32:03,108 --> 00:32:04,248
(What is Team YB eating?)

930
00:32:04,308 --> 00:32:05,308
A boxed meal?

931
00:32:05,309 --> 00:32:06,624
I heard that they're getting boxed meals.

932
00:32:06,648 --> 00:32:07,717
Right.

933
00:32:07,718 --> 00:32:09,078
I wonder what's in the boxed meal.

934
00:32:09,648 --> 00:32:10,648
What kind of boxed meal?

935
00:32:11,118 --> 00:32:12,687
Did they go to the deserted island?

936
00:32:12,688 --> 00:32:14,394
(What's the boxed meal that the losing team is eating?)

937
00:32:14,418 --> 00:32:16,287
I've never tried it before.

938
00:32:16,288 --> 00:32:17,787
Me neither. I've never had it.

939
00:32:17,788 --> 00:32:19,164
(Team YB is still on their way to the deserted island.)

940
00:32:19,188 --> 00:32:21,598
You went easy on the older guys.

941
00:32:21,998 --> 00:32:24,867
- What?
- You went easy on them.

942
00:32:24,868 --> 00:32:26,497
To be honest, I did my best.

943
00:32:26,498 --> 00:32:27,668
(He never went easy on them.)

944
00:32:28,068 --> 00:32:29,297
No matter what...

945
00:32:29,298 --> 00:32:31,184
You probably don't believe me, but I also did my best.

946
00:32:31,208 --> 00:32:32,838
- What?
- During the match,

947
00:32:33,208 --> 00:32:34,838
my feet kept sinking in.

948
00:32:35,008 --> 00:32:36,478
So I couldn't help but fall.

949
00:32:37,678 --> 00:32:39,407
(I guess we were destined to go to the deserted island.)

950
00:32:39,408 --> 00:32:40,977
I'm sure he set everything up.

951
00:32:40,978 --> 00:32:42,677
He was on the deserted island for eight hours.

952
00:32:42,678 --> 00:32:43,847
He must've done something.

953
00:32:43,848 --> 00:32:45,117
Right.

954
00:32:45,118 --> 00:32:46,687
If he didn't do anything during eight hours,

955
00:32:46,688 --> 00:32:48,087
- then he was just slacking off.
- It'd be a piece of cake.

956
00:32:48,088 --> 00:32:49,757
I'm sure he did everything. It's Yong Jin.

957
00:32:49,758 --> 00:32:51,187
He must've done everything.

958
00:32:51,188 --> 00:32:53,034
- He was there for eight hours.
- It's possible...

959
00:32:53,058 --> 00:32:55,097
that Yong Jin built a house.

960
00:32:55,098 --> 00:32:56,174
(Arriving at the deserted island)

961
00:32:56,198 --> 00:32:57,598
We'd better be careful.

962
00:32:59,368 --> 00:33:01,938
(Darkness settles over the deserted island.)

963
00:33:02,468 --> 00:33:04,907
(The fact that it's uninhabited feels more real.)

964
00:33:04,908 --> 00:33:06,807
What did he build and where?

965
00:33:06,808 --> 00:33:07,878
(He's given up.)

966
00:33:08,508 --> 00:33:11,277
(The boat leaves the island.)

967
00:33:11,278 --> 00:33:12,977
Welcome to the deserted island.

968
00:33:12,978 --> 00:33:13,978
(Ki Taek, DinDin, and Joon check in.)

969
00:33:13,979 --> 00:33:16,447
We prepared a welcome kit for you.

970
00:33:16,448 --> 00:33:17,948
- Okay.
- Here you go.

971
00:33:18,588 --> 00:33:20,228
- What's inside?
- Please go up this way.

972
00:33:20,288 --> 00:33:22,458
There are only flashlights and boxed meals.

973
00:33:22,788 --> 00:33:24,157
There's gochujang.

974
00:33:24,158 --> 00:33:25,158
(3-tier boxed meal, flashlights)

975
00:33:25,159 --> 00:33:26,458
There's gochujang.

976
00:33:27,458 --> 00:33:28,697
Let's take one flashlight each.

977
00:33:28,698 --> 00:33:30,468
Over there,

978
00:33:30,768 --> 00:33:32,198
you'll see the shovels.

979
00:33:32,298 --> 00:33:33,637
Make sure to take one with you.

980
00:33:33,638 --> 00:33:35,267
Would this be useful?

981
00:33:35,268 --> 00:33:37,738
(Why would we need a shovel?)

982
00:33:37,908 --> 00:33:39,038
Why would it be useful?

983
00:33:39,568 --> 00:33:40,907
That's for the restroom.

984
00:33:40,908 --> 00:33:42,188
- What?
- It's for the restroom.

985
00:33:43,478 --> 00:33:44,678
We have to dig before pooping?

986
00:33:44,808 --> 00:33:46,747
- What?
- We have to dig before pooping?

987
00:33:46,748 --> 00:33:47,848
Yes.

988
00:33:48,248 --> 00:33:49,677
Is this going to be okay?

989
00:33:49,678 --> 00:33:51,518
(There isn't even a restroom.)

990
00:33:51,648 --> 00:33:53,247
It's better to hold it.

991
00:33:53,248 --> 00:33:54,958
Right, I'll just hold it.

992
00:33:55,158 --> 00:33:57,527
Everything is possible by controlling the mind.

993
00:33:57,528 --> 00:33:58,587
Things turn out the way you think.

994
00:33:58,588 --> 00:34:00,104
- We have to hold it.
- Is it this way?

995
00:34:00,128 --> 00:34:01,697
Yes, go up to the base camp.

996
00:34:01,698 --> 00:34:02,727
We'll go up.

997
00:34:02,728 --> 00:34:03,927
So this isn't the base camp.

998
00:34:03,928 --> 00:34:05,397
It's been very tiring today.

999
00:34:05,398 --> 00:34:07,738
By the way, we might not sleep here tonight.

1000
00:34:07,868 --> 00:34:09,137
It's a cliff here.

1001
00:34:09,138 --> 00:34:10,838
(Yong Jin must have built a house.)

1002
00:34:11,538 --> 00:34:13,678
This place is perfect to shoot a horror film.

1003
00:34:14,208 --> 00:34:16,908
(They walk through the darkness to head to the base camp.)

1004
00:34:17,608 --> 00:34:18,678
Hold on.

1005
00:34:19,578 --> 00:34:21,578
What did Yong Jin make exactly?

1006
00:34:22,418 --> 00:34:24,017
What did Yong Jin make?

1007
00:34:24,018 --> 00:34:26,047
What is this?

1008
00:34:26,048 --> 00:34:27,057
(The base camp is emptier than they expected.)

1009
00:34:27,058 --> 00:34:28,388
He just slacked off.

1010
00:34:29,288 --> 00:34:30,857
This is all he did for eight hours?

1011
00:34:30,858 --> 00:34:32,128
- What's this?
- Is this it?

1012
00:34:32,628 --> 00:34:33,797
Is this it?

1013
00:34:33,798 --> 00:34:35,498
He spent eight hours making this?

1014
00:34:36,698 --> 00:34:38,627
I'm genuinely shocked.

1015
00:34:38,628 --> 00:34:39,667
(A huge shock)

1016
00:34:39,668 --> 00:34:40,668
- What's this?
- Tonight...

1017
00:34:40,669 --> 00:34:41,937
we have to sleep here.

1018
00:34:41,938 --> 00:34:44,208
He just made this during eight hours?

1019
00:34:45,068 --> 00:34:47,307
(Ki Taek is also very disappointed.)

1020
00:34:47,308 --> 00:34:48,337
Wait a minute.

1021
00:34:48,338 --> 00:34:50,307
We need to call Se Yoon about this.

1022
00:34:50,308 --> 00:34:51,468
(I should call and complain.)

1023
00:34:51,708 --> 00:34:53,347
(Making a complaint call)

1024
00:34:53,348 --> 00:34:55,118
His ringback tone is really...

1025
00:34:55,848 --> 00:34:57,588
(Even his ringback tone is annoying.)

1026
00:34:57,748 --> 00:34:59,547
A local resident shouted from a distance,

1027
00:34:59,548 --> 00:35:01,387
"It's dangerous over there," but they pulled him out.

1028
00:35:01,388 --> 00:35:02,417
(A video call)

1029
00:35:02,418 --> 00:35:04,987
DinDin is calling me. Can't he get his screen time alone?

1030
00:35:04,988 --> 00:35:06,268
He can't do it without our help.

1031
00:35:06,898 --> 00:35:08,357
(Pick it up now.)

1032
00:35:08,358 --> 00:35:09,897
What's going on?

1033
00:35:09,898 --> 00:35:11,228
Can you accept the video call?

1034
00:35:11,728 --> 00:35:13,897
I'm sorry, but I'm not wearing makeup.

1035
00:35:13,898 --> 00:35:14,898
I don't want the video call.

1036
00:35:14,898 --> 00:35:15,898
Just accept it.

1037
00:35:17,038 --> 00:35:19,138
- What?
- Accept my video call.

1038
00:35:19,908 --> 00:35:21,177
He sounds very angry.

1039
00:35:21,178 --> 00:35:22,438
Why is he so aggressive?

1040
00:35:22,938 --> 00:35:25,278
You punk, learn your manners before calling me again.

1041
00:35:25,508 --> 00:35:26,748
Accept my call!

1042
00:35:27,148 --> 00:35:28,678
He has no manners at all.

1043
00:35:29,278 --> 00:35:31,518
- That was so rude.
- It was impolite.

1044
00:35:31,688 --> 00:35:34,157
Don't you have manners in Canada? How dare he?

1045
00:35:34,158 --> 00:35:35,158
(He has no manners on the phone.)

1046
00:35:35,159 --> 00:35:36,388
Hello?

1047
00:35:36,488 --> 00:35:39,128
- Can you be on video call?
- Based on reporting principles...

1048
00:35:39,358 --> 00:35:41,658
Are you available for a video call?

1049
00:35:42,698 --> 00:35:44,128
- Video call?
- Yes.

1050
00:35:45,028 --> 00:35:46,028
Are you making a request?

1051
00:35:47,168 --> 00:35:49,097
- Yes.
- All right.

1052
00:35:49,098 --> 00:35:51,007
You should tell me your name first. Introduce yourself.

1053
00:35:51,008 --> 00:35:52,438
This is Cheol.

1054
00:35:53,238 --> 00:35:54,537
All right.

1055
00:35:54,538 --> 00:35:55,678
I'll pick it up.

1056
00:35:57,048 --> 00:35:58,677
(He finally accepts the video call.)

1057
00:35:58,678 --> 00:36:00,318
- What's going on?
- Sir.

1058
00:36:01,778 --> 00:36:02,948
What is this?

1059
00:36:03,888 --> 00:36:05,487
The architect is right next to me,

1060
00:36:05,488 --> 00:36:06,647
so I'll pass the phone over to him.

1061
00:36:06,648 --> 00:36:08,517
What were you doing for eight hours?

1062
00:36:08,518 --> 00:36:10,627
(Architect Lee Yong Jin appears.)

1063
00:36:10,628 --> 00:36:12,928
Is this all you did during eight hours?

1064
00:36:13,598 --> 00:36:14,857
My gosh.

1065
00:36:14,858 --> 00:36:16,557
- If that's how you'll talk...
- Hang up if he keeps being rude.

1066
00:36:16,558 --> 00:36:18,127
- That's quite disappointing.
- Right.

1067
00:36:18,128 --> 00:36:19,798
You brat, how dare you?

1068
00:36:20,498 --> 00:36:21,897
- Don't be rude.
- You punk.

1069
00:36:21,898 --> 00:36:24,037
You brat, I didn't take six hours to make it.

1070
00:36:24,038 --> 00:36:25,038
It took me an hour.

1071
00:36:25,039 --> 00:36:26,167
(Telling the truth)

1072
00:36:26,168 --> 00:36:27,337
(Gosh, he's so annoying.)

1073
00:36:27,338 --> 00:36:28,338
He did something else.

1074
00:36:28,339 --> 00:36:29,808
How can I spend six hours on that?

1075
00:36:30,038 --> 00:36:32,647
What did you do during the remaining time?

1076
00:36:32,648 --> 00:36:33,918
I just killed time.

1077
00:36:35,848 --> 00:36:36,987
(This is infuriating.)

1078
00:36:36,988 --> 00:36:37,988
He looks annoyed.

1079
00:36:38,918 --> 00:36:40,787
Can you show us the conger eel?

1080
00:36:40,788 --> 00:36:41,957
(Ki Taek is curious about the conger eel.)

1081
00:36:41,958 --> 00:36:43,417
But we finished it.

1082
00:36:43,418 --> 00:36:44,957
I wish you could've had some.

1083
00:36:44,958 --> 00:36:46,087
(Hanging up)

1084
00:36:46,088 --> 00:36:47,527
I wish you could've had some.

1085
00:36:47,528 --> 00:36:49,358
(Hanging up because he feels jealous)

1086
00:36:49,998 --> 00:36:52,238
- It looks delicious.
- They're practically on vacation.

1087
00:36:52,298 --> 00:36:53,637
Want to see the lettuce?

1088
00:36:53,638 --> 00:36:54,968
The lettuce is this big.

1089
00:36:55,238 --> 00:36:56,297
What? They hung up.

1090
00:36:56,298 --> 00:36:57,608
These punks.

1091
00:36:58,008 --> 00:36:59,537
Gosh, that's good.

1092
00:36:59,538 --> 00:37:01,298
(Their last dance on the food table starts.)

1093
00:37:01,478 --> 00:37:03,577
That's real craftsmanship.

1094
00:37:03,578 --> 00:37:04,607
(Here comes the master's technique.)

1095
00:37:04,608 --> 00:37:07,077
Even if we don't finish it, we should still taste it.

1096
00:37:07,078 --> 00:37:08,838
(An effortless yet precise hand of a master)

1097
00:37:09,548 --> 00:37:10,588
This is it.

1098
00:37:11,018 --> 00:37:12,118
This is the best.

1099
00:37:13,188 --> 00:37:14,717
Is it possible to enjoy food this much?

1100
00:37:14,718 --> 00:37:16,198
(Moon Se Yoon's fried rice is ready.)

1101
00:37:16,658 --> 00:37:18,257
- Go.
- Wait for ten seconds.

1102
00:37:18,258 --> 00:37:19,258
(10 seconds of letting it rest)

1103
00:37:19,259 --> 00:37:20,328
Nine...

1104
00:37:20,728 --> 00:37:22,127
(Good things come...)

1105
00:37:22,128 --> 00:37:24,028
(to those who wait.)

1106
00:37:24,168 --> 00:37:26,897
- The last dance.
- Okay, it's the last dance.

1107
00:37:26,898 --> 00:37:27,967
Scrape it.

1108
00:37:27,968 --> 00:37:30,408
(As soon as he's done talking, they attack with their spoon.)

1109
00:37:30,708 --> 00:37:32,968
(A dessert is a must no matter how full you are.)

1110
00:37:33,908 --> 00:37:35,708
(This is a signature dessert for Koreans.)

1111
00:37:36,948 --> 00:37:38,048
It's tasty.

1112
00:37:38,608 --> 00:37:39,907
I can still eat.

1113
00:37:39,908 --> 00:37:41,828
(Even if you're full, you can't stop eating it.)

1114
00:37:43,418 --> 00:37:44,447
It's rich.

1115
00:37:44,448 --> 00:37:46,957
(The seasoning is perfect even for the cook.)

1116
00:37:46,958 --> 00:37:47,988
It's delicious.

1117
00:37:48,418 --> 00:37:49,587
Gosh, it's good.

1118
00:37:49,588 --> 00:37:51,204
(They cleared the conger eel course meal completely.)

1119
00:37:51,228 --> 00:37:52,557
What has he done?

1120
00:37:52,558 --> 00:37:53,727
We went trekking.

1121
00:37:53,728 --> 00:37:55,797
Then let's sleep while sitting down.

1122
00:37:55,798 --> 00:37:56,927
(We won't make anything either.)

1123
00:37:56,928 --> 00:37:58,297
What on earth is this?

1124
00:37:58,298 --> 00:37:59,867
He didn't even clean up after himself.

1125
00:37:59,868 --> 00:38:00,868
(Declaring a strike)

1126
00:38:01,198 --> 00:38:03,908
- What kind of attitude is this?
- What's this?

1127
00:38:04,438 --> 00:38:06,437
This is a bit harsh.

1128
00:38:06,438 --> 00:38:07,807
(Joon and DinDin are furious.)

1129
00:38:07,808 --> 00:38:09,608
Should I take them all out and flip them?

1130
00:38:10,008 --> 00:38:11,607
What's this?

1131
00:38:11,608 --> 00:38:13,007
We ate a lot of hijiki earlier.

1132
00:38:13,008 --> 00:38:14,017
(Inside the 3-tier boxed meal)

1133
00:38:14,018 --> 00:38:17,118
Each tier is filled with ridiculous ingredients.

1134
00:38:17,288 --> 00:38:18,517
They don't go well together.

1135
00:38:18,518 --> 00:38:19,518
(It's only filled with seaweed.)

1136
00:38:19,519 --> 00:38:21,288
When you said it was a boxed meal,

1137
00:38:21,788 --> 00:38:23,558
I thought that it was a regular one.

1138
00:38:23,858 --> 00:38:24,987
(Very disappointed)

1139
00:38:24,988 --> 00:38:26,127
(Growling)

1140
00:38:26,128 --> 00:38:28,657
Ki Taek, your stomach is grumbling...

1141
00:38:28,658 --> 00:38:29,738
even after looking at this.

1142
00:38:29,928 --> 00:38:30,928
That's impressive.

1143
00:38:30,929 --> 00:38:32,827
Can I get an insert shot before you eat it?

1144
00:38:32,828 --> 00:38:33,837
Sure.

1145
00:38:33,838 --> 00:38:35,938
- Is this worth it?
- Why would you film this?

1146
00:38:36,738 --> 00:38:38,284
What would you get an insert shot of this?

1147
00:38:38,308 --> 00:38:41,137
- We can't make it anymore.
- Just film the sea instead.

1148
00:38:41,138 --> 00:38:42,607
It's a specialty, so it's hard to find.

1149
00:38:42,608 --> 00:38:43,777
(These are hard to find.)

1150
00:38:43,778 --> 00:38:46,208
(We'll explain since we're filming it.)

1151
00:38:46,248 --> 00:38:48,878
(In the 1st tier are hijiki and seaweed.)

1152
00:38:49,548 --> 00:38:51,648
(In the 2nd tier is red algae.)

1153
00:38:52,618 --> 00:38:54,658
(In the 3rd tier is white rice.)

1154
00:38:55,188 --> 00:38:57,558
(A 3-item boxed meal with specialties from Wando)

1155
00:38:57,888 --> 00:39:01,097
(And a tiny packet of gochujang)

1156
00:39:01,098 --> 00:39:03,198
There's so little gochujang.

1157
00:39:03,428 --> 00:39:06,498
Compared to this much rice...

1158
00:39:06,698 --> 00:39:08,068
It's an in-flight meal.

1159
00:39:08,438 --> 00:39:10,567
Based on what we see,

1160
00:39:10,568 --> 00:39:11,807
instead of enjoying the food,

1161
00:39:11,808 --> 00:39:13,007
let's plan our revenge.

1162
00:39:13,008 --> 00:39:14,507
- Thank you for the food.
- What do you think?

1163
00:39:14,508 --> 00:39:17,077
To make them pay back...

1164
00:39:17,078 --> 00:39:18,777
and get even with them,

1165
00:39:18,778 --> 00:39:19,907
let's come up with a plan.

1166
00:39:19,908 --> 00:39:25,588
(Wait and see, Yong Jin and Se Yoon.)

1167
00:39:26,488 --> 00:39:30,788
(Like red algae with gochujang on it)

1168
00:39:31,928 --> 00:39:34,598
(We'll chew you into pieces.)

1169
00:39:34,758 --> 00:39:37,028
Don't you think lunch was better?

1170
00:39:37,798 --> 00:39:39,167
This looks better.

1171
00:39:39,168 --> 00:39:40,228
I agree with you.

1172
00:39:40,368 --> 00:39:42,937
It's poorer than what I expected.

1173
00:39:42,938 --> 00:39:44,107
(They get more desperate about their revenge.)

1174
00:39:44,108 --> 00:39:45,138
Don't you think?

1175
00:39:45,668 --> 00:39:47,438
It might get soggy in the stomach.

1176
00:39:47,638 --> 00:39:48,938
I must have been hungry.

1177
00:39:49,438 --> 00:39:50,477
This is good.

1178
00:39:50,478 --> 00:39:51,708
- Really?
- Yes.

1179
00:39:52,248 --> 00:39:53,408
You know what?

1180
00:39:53,878 --> 00:39:56,017
- I think it's because of gochujang.
- It's delicious.

1181
00:39:56,018 --> 00:39:57,988
With some gochujang...

1182
00:39:58,688 --> 00:40:01,287
When you take a bite, there's a strong smell of the sea.

1183
00:40:01,288 --> 00:40:02,618
Is this a type of seaweed?

1184
00:40:03,418 --> 00:40:04,627
It tastes like ramyeon.

1185
00:40:04,628 --> 00:40:05,927
(He actually enjoys it with a dip of gochujang.)

1186
00:40:05,928 --> 00:40:07,128
- And so...
- Samhap.

1187
00:40:08,028 --> 00:40:10,228
- Isn't it good?
- Taste it carefully. It's good.

1188
00:40:11,698 --> 00:40:14,597
(They run out of gochujang.)

1189
00:40:14,598 --> 00:40:15,737
It tastes bland now.

1190
00:40:15,738 --> 00:40:17,408
(It's bland without gochujang.)

1191
00:40:17,708 --> 00:40:19,908
Can you give us more gochujang?

1192
00:40:20,408 --> 00:40:22,237
Why don't we add...

1193
00:40:22,238 --> 00:40:23,577
some water to it?

1194
00:40:23,578 --> 00:40:24,578
What do you think?

1195
00:40:24,579 --> 00:40:25,707
(The new member's desperate look)

1196
00:40:25,708 --> 00:40:27,578
Speaking as the most senior member,

1197
00:40:28,278 --> 00:40:30,817
we can't get through work after a meal like this.

1198
00:40:30,818 --> 00:40:32,188
We need something more.

1199
00:40:32,718 --> 00:40:33,718
You have something, don't you?

1200
00:40:33,719 --> 00:40:34,918
(Eating)

1201
00:40:35,158 --> 00:40:36,858
This is not enough.

1202
00:40:37,188 --> 00:40:38,628
With this little food,

1203
00:40:38,828 --> 00:40:40,227
you won't get anything out of us.

1204
00:40:40,228 --> 00:40:41,898
Stop enjoying it.

1205
00:40:43,198 --> 00:40:44,427
I'm trying to negotiate.

1206
00:40:44,428 --> 00:40:46,728
(His eating doesn't help with the threat.)

1207
00:40:46,828 --> 00:40:48,897
This little food won't do.

1208
00:40:48,898 --> 00:40:50,168
We're too exhausted.

1209
00:40:50,338 --> 00:40:52,768
Can we play another game like Lighting the Ogre's Flame?

1210
00:40:52,838 --> 00:40:54,337
We can play Lighting the Ogre's Flame again.

1211
00:40:54,338 --> 00:40:55,607
That's a great game.

1212
00:40:55,608 --> 00:40:56,977
- Yes.
- I like Ogre's Flame.

1213
00:40:56,978 --> 00:40:58,208
We can play that again.

1214
00:40:58,548 --> 00:41:01,217
(However, the production crew didn't prepare any more food.)

1215
00:41:01,218 --> 00:41:02,817
I emptied out my pockets...

1216
00:41:02,818 --> 00:41:04,048
- and found this.
- A sausage?

1217
00:41:04,888 --> 00:41:06,017
- A sausage?
- What is it?

1218
00:41:06,018 --> 00:41:07,087
I just found this.

1219
00:41:07,088 --> 00:41:08,088
(He managed to find a sausage.)

1220
00:41:08,089 --> 00:41:10,188
How about a pull-up challenge to show your loyalty?

1221
00:41:10,558 --> 00:41:12,927
What? Loyalty pull-up?

1222
00:41:12,928 --> 00:41:14,327
- Loyalty pull-up.
- What's that?

1223
00:41:14,328 --> 00:41:15,857
- What is that?
- There's a pull-up bar over there.

1224
00:41:15,858 --> 00:41:18,628
- Okay.
- The three of you must do...

1225
00:41:19,028 --> 00:41:20,127
a total of 30 pull-ups.

1226
00:41:20,128 --> 00:41:21,467
- Gosh.
- We can't even do three.

1227
00:41:21,468 --> 00:41:22,897
Let's give it a try.

1228
00:41:22,898 --> 00:41:24,238
Let's try it anyway.

1229
00:41:24,368 --> 00:41:25,837
Even if we don't make it, we won't lose anything.

1230
00:41:25,838 --> 00:41:28,077
It's a chance to win the sausage. Let's try it.

1231
00:41:28,078 --> 00:41:29,208
What is it?

1232
00:41:29,708 --> 00:41:31,078
Let's do it.

1233
00:41:31,148 --> 00:41:32,708
It's a small one.

1234
00:41:33,148 --> 00:41:34,478
A small one.

1235
00:41:35,878 --> 00:41:37,188
The viewers are watching you.

1236
00:41:38,618 --> 00:41:41,488
(Booing at the thoughtful celebrity)

1237
00:41:41,918 --> 00:41:44,257
(He returns it meekly.)

1238
00:41:44,258 --> 00:41:45,587
- A sausage?
- Yes, it is.

1239
00:41:45,588 --> 00:41:47,458
He's just trying to create a good scene.

1240
00:41:47,728 --> 00:41:49,127
- It's a small one?
- It's a good move.

1241
00:41:49,128 --> 00:41:50,128
(I just did it to make it funny.)

1242
00:41:50,129 --> 00:41:52,097
- Shall we go?
- It's quite big.

1243
00:41:52,098 --> 00:41:53,098
- Let's go.
- Okay.

1244
00:41:53,099 --> 00:41:54,637
How do we do 30 reps?

1245
00:41:54,638 --> 00:41:57,238
- I don't think I can even do three.
- I'll go last. No pressure.

1246
00:41:57,668 --> 00:41:59,807
By the way, what qualifies as a proper chin-up?

1247
00:41:59,808 --> 00:42:01,737
Is using momentum allowed? Regular gym-goers...

1248
00:42:01,738 --> 00:42:02,738
have different standards, you know.

1249
00:42:02,739 --> 00:42:05,047
- Using momentum is allowed.
- We can use momentum.

1250
00:42:05,048 --> 00:42:08,717
And we don't have to fully extend our arms, right?

1251
00:42:08,718 --> 00:42:10,987
We'll stick to average folks' standards for a proper rep, okay?

1252
00:42:10,988 --> 00:42:12,188
- I'll go first.
- Okay.

1253
00:42:12,448 --> 00:42:14,217
You see,

1254
00:42:14,218 --> 00:42:15,357
I have a chin-up bar...

1255
00:42:15,358 --> 00:42:17,558
set up at home.

1256
00:42:18,228 --> 00:42:20,257
I heard that just hanging from the bar...

1257
00:42:20,258 --> 00:42:22,427
helps to improve shoulder flexibility.

1258
00:42:22,428 --> 00:42:24,927
So I often just hang from the bar.

1259
00:42:24,928 --> 00:42:26,727
And I do chin-ups quite often as well.

1260
00:42:26,728 --> 00:42:27,937
I do them whenever I can.

1261
00:42:27,938 --> 00:42:28,938
How many chin-ups do you want me to do?

1262
00:42:28,938 --> 00:42:29,938
(He's full of confidence.)

1263
00:42:29,939 --> 00:42:31,707
- Just do ten reps.
- I'll begin.

1264
00:42:31,708 --> 00:42:33,567
(Will he do as many chin-ups as he is confident?)

1265
00:42:33,568 --> 00:42:35,438
- Let's eat the sausage. One.
- One.

1266
00:42:36,078 --> 00:42:37,138
- Two.
- Two.

1267
00:42:37,578 --> 00:42:38,578
- Three.
- Three.

1268
00:42:38,579 --> 00:42:40,718
- Great! Keep it going, and hit ten.
- Four.

1269
00:42:40,978 --> 00:42:42,738
- Great! Keep it going, and hit ten.
- Four.

1270
00:42:42,948 --> 00:42:45,817
- Five.
- Five. Don't stop. Just one more.

1271
00:42:45,818 --> 00:42:46,818
Just do one more.

1272
00:42:46,819 --> 00:42:47,987
Just one more.

1273
00:42:47,988 --> 00:42:49,018
Think about the sausage.

1274
00:42:50,218 --> 00:42:51,758
That's good. Great job.

1275
00:42:51,858 --> 00:42:53,058
Just do a muscle-up.

1276
00:42:53,228 --> 00:42:54,358
Just do a muscle-up.

1277
00:42:55,798 --> 00:42:58,127
(That's far from enough to do a chin-up.)

1278
00:42:58,128 --> 00:43:00,297
- DinDin.
- Pull yourself up. That's good...

1279
00:43:00,298 --> 00:43:01,638
- Oh, no.
- I was losing my grip.

1280
00:43:01,738 --> 00:43:02,997
I was losing my grip. Goodness.

1281
00:43:02,998 --> 00:43:04,007
(DinDin only managed to do 5 chin-ups.)

1282
00:43:04,008 --> 00:43:06,184
I could've done more, but it's just that the bar is too high for me.

1283
00:43:06,208 --> 00:43:07,208
You've done a lot.

1284
00:43:07,908 --> 00:43:09,437
You'll pull it off...

1285
00:43:09,438 --> 00:43:11,148
if you just stop tensing up.

1286
00:43:11,608 --> 00:43:13,347
(Ki Taek touches the bar.)

1287
00:43:13,348 --> 00:43:15,077
It's harder to hold onto this bar than the ones at the gym.

1288
00:43:15,078 --> 00:43:16,377
(He puts the stool away?)

1289
00:43:16,378 --> 00:43:17,617
- Hey...
- Ki Taek, be careful.

1290
00:43:17,618 --> 00:43:18,717
- You...
- There's a cliff behind you.

1291
00:43:18,718 --> 00:43:20,557
Why did you put that away?

1292
00:43:20,558 --> 00:43:22,687
I thought I might kick it with my feet.

1293
00:43:22,688 --> 00:43:23,717
(I thought I might kick it with my feet.)

1294
00:43:23,718 --> 00:43:25,788
- Oh, really?
- That's why.

1295
00:43:26,288 --> 00:43:28,327
- I can reach the bar without it.
- I see.

1296
00:43:28,328 --> 00:43:30,497
Just so you know, I'm really bad at chin-ups.

1297
00:43:30,498 --> 00:43:31,728
Hold on. Let me check.

1298
00:43:33,398 --> 00:43:34,797
- See? You can reach it too.
- Oh, I can reach it.

1299
00:43:34,798 --> 00:43:35,798
I can't reach it.

1300
00:43:36,638 --> 00:43:38,567
(Strangely, he feels defeated.)

1301
00:43:38,568 --> 00:43:40,337
Ki Taek, do you work out regularly?

1302
00:43:40,338 --> 00:43:42,107
Joon, he said he had gone to gym...

1303
00:43:42,108 --> 00:43:43,277
after the shoot for this show.

1304
00:43:43,278 --> 00:43:44,807
- Just once.
- He likes it more than I do.

1305
00:43:44,808 --> 00:43:47,317
Judging by his words, you'd think he's a workout king.

1306
00:43:47,318 --> 00:43:48,318
- Right?
- Yes.

1307
00:43:48,319 --> 00:43:50,217
I work out just to build up my stamina.

1308
00:43:50,218 --> 00:43:51,848
I often pull an all-nighter for a shoot.

1309
00:43:52,148 --> 00:43:53,587
That's why I work out regularly.

1310
00:43:53,588 --> 00:43:55,017
- Exactly. Show us what you've got.
- Just to build up my stamina.

1311
00:43:55,018 --> 00:43:56,917
He went to gym after the shoot for this show.

1312
00:43:56,918 --> 00:43:58,587
He's basically a workout addict.

1313
00:43:58,588 --> 00:44:00,897
- He's just like Jong Kook.
- That's right.

1314
00:44:00,898 --> 00:44:03,327
He's the Kim Jong Kook of 2 Days 1 Night.

1315
00:44:03,328 --> 00:44:04,797
- You're right.
- I'll begin.

1316
00:44:04,798 --> 00:44:05,702
(Could he really be the workout king?)

1317
00:44:05,736 --> 00:44:07,173
No, I'm not good at this. I'll begin.

1318
00:44:07,197 --> 00:44:08,626
Go, Ki Taek. You've got this.

1319
00:44:08,627 --> 00:44:10,366
(Current Tally: 6 out of 30)

1320
00:44:10,367 --> 00:44:13,096
(He's doing strict-form chin-ups!)

1321
00:44:13,097 --> 00:44:14,936
Hey, stop doing strict chin-ups!

1322
00:44:14,937 --> 00:44:16,236
- Don't do strict chin-ups.
- Got it.

1323
00:44:16,237 --> 00:44:17,736
- Just cut corners.
- Three.

1324
00:44:17,737 --> 00:44:19,257
Cut some corners. Cheat a little more.

1325
00:44:19,407 --> 00:44:20,607
Cheat a little more.

1326
00:44:20,777 --> 00:44:22,207
Cheat a little more... That's good.

1327
00:44:22,437 --> 00:44:23,477
Five.

1328
00:44:23,507 --> 00:44:25,176
(Current Tally: 12 out of 30)

1329
00:44:25,177 --> 00:44:26,246
Good. We're going to pull this off.

1330
00:44:26,247 --> 00:44:27,346
Yes. That's great.

1331
00:44:27,347 --> 00:44:28,376
(His face looks like it's going to explode.)

1332
00:44:28,377 --> 00:44:29,446
- That's good.
- Nine.

1333
00:44:29,447 --> 00:44:30,486
(He's done a whopping 9 reps so far.)

1334
00:44:30,487 --> 00:44:31,886
He's really tall.

1335
00:44:31,887 --> 00:44:33,557
(Shall I do just one more?)

1336
00:44:35,111 --> 00:44:36,250
That doesn't count.

1337
00:44:36,251 --> 00:44:37,620
- He says it doesn't count.
- You've done nine reps so far.

1338
00:44:37,621 --> 00:44:39,121
- Why?
- Nine reps so far.

1339
00:44:39,251 --> 00:44:41,251
Why? Aren't you too strict? All right.

1340
00:44:41,391 --> 00:44:42,891
Gosh. I can't pull myself up.

1341
00:44:42,921 --> 00:44:45,361
You can do this, Ki Taek. Lee Ki Taek!

1342
00:44:46,691 --> 00:44:48,691
(All right. I, Lee Ki Taek...)

1343
00:44:49,031 --> 00:44:50,701
(shall hit 10 chin-ups.)

1344
00:44:51,301 --> 00:44:54,131
(Squeeze out every last ounce of strength!)

1345
00:44:54,301 --> 00:44:55,500
- Hey.
- Just one more... I can't do it.

1346
00:44:55,501 --> 00:44:57,581
- I couldn't do any more reps.
- His record is nine.

1347
00:44:57,641 --> 00:44:59,040
- Then the tally is 14.
- He did 9 reps.

1348
00:44:59,041 --> 00:45:00,370
- We'll pull this off.
- How many should I do?

1349
00:45:00,371 --> 00:45:01,911
Joon will do strict chin-ups.

1350
00:45:02,941 --> 00:45:03,941
He'll do strict chin-ups.

1351
00:45:04,111 --> 00:45:06,750
He'll lock out his arms completely and then pull back up.

1352
00:45:06,751 --> 00:45:08,680
I'm sorry, but after my "Catch Catch" challenge,

1353
00:45:08,681 --> 00:45:09,850
I was shocked.

1354
00:45:09,851 --> 00:45:13,150
It's because I looked short and fat.

1355
00:45:13,151 --> 00:45:15,220
So I haven't worked out in a month.

1356
00:45:15,221 --> 00:45:16,260
Don't worry about it.

1357
00:45:16,261 --> 00:45:18,721
I lost ton of muscle so fast and went weak.

1358
00:45:19,491 --> 00:45:22,131
(It's hard to do 16 chin-ups even if you don't do them strictly.)

1359
00:45:22,291 --> 00:45:23,730
(Will the gym owner be able to pull it off?)

1360
00:45:23,731 --> 00:45:24,761
I'll begin.

1361
00:45:24,801 --> 00:45:26,370
(Current Tally: 14 out of 30)

1362
00:45:26,371 --> 00:45:28,170
- One, two...
- One, two,

1363
00:45:28,171 --> 00:45:30,270
- three, four, - Don't drop down so low.

1364
00:45:30,271 --> 00:45:32,270
Five, six,

1365
00:45:32,271 --> 00:45:34,370
seven, eight...

1366
00:45:34,371 --> 00:45:36,040
That's great. Nine, ten.

1367
00:45:36,041 --> 00:45:37,810
- Don't drop down so low.
- One,

1368
00:45:37,811 --> 00:45:40,250
- two, three, - He'll pull it off.

1369
00:45:40,251 --> 00:45:42,211
- four, five...
- Four, five...

1370
00:45:42,951 --> 00:45:44,827
- One more!
- I think I can easily pull it off.

1371
00:45:44,851 --> 00:45:46,420
- Really?
- I'll do a strict chin-up now.

1372
00:45:46,421 --> 00:45:47,651
This is a strict chin-up.

1373
00:45:48,121 --> 00:45:49,560
(Joon, the gym owner, succeeded in doing 16 chin-ups.)

1374
00:45:49,561 --> 00:45:51,020
(Amazed)

1375
00:45:51,021 --> 00:45:52,090
It's a piece of cake.

1376
00:45:52,091 --> 00:45:53,091
(His muscles are still there.)

1377
00:45:53,091 --> 00:45:54,091
You've completed your mission.

1378
00:45:54,092 --> 00:45:55,390
(They successfully obtained a sausage.)

1379
00:45:55,391 --> 00:45:58,031
We made it. I think I could've done 16 reps even in a strict form.

1380
00:45:58,061 --> 00:45:59,901
I have an idea. Hear me out.

1381
00:46:00,431 --> 00:46:02,170
- See this red line here?
- Yes.

1382
00:46:02,171 --> 00:46:04,540
Let's spin the sausage in the air, and when it falls on the ground,

1383
00:46:04,541 --> 00:46:05,900
whoever this end points at gets to eat first.

1384
00:46:05,901 --> 00:46:07,240
- Okay. Sounds good.
- What do you say?

1385
00:46:07,241 --> 00:46:08,540
- That's a good idea?
- Do you like the idea?

1386
00:46:08,541 --> 00:46:10,110
- It's a loyalty game.
- Exactly.

1387
00:46:10,111 --> 00:46:11,111
Good.

1388
00:46:11,112 --> 00:46:12,432
Hee Sung, can you spin it for us?

1389
00:46:13,381 --> 00:46:14,381
Sausage!

1390
00:46:17,151 --> 00:46:18,421
(It points at Ki Taek!)

1391
00:46:18,581 --> 00:46:20,020
- Just remember that feeling.
- Hold on.

1392
00:46:20,021 --> 00:46:21,420
- Wait. Stay still.
- Stay still.

1393
00:46:21,421 --> 00:46:22,990
You were standing over here.

1394
00:46:22,991 --> 00:46:25,220
- No, I wasn't.
- You were standing over here.

1395
00:46:25,221 --> 00:46:26,660
Wait. Hold on.

1396
00:46:26,661 --> 00:46:27,690
Stay still, okay?

1397
00:46:27,691 --> 00:46:29,307
(DinDin is being persistent and ridiculous.)

1398
00:46:29,331 --> 00:46:30,400
(Blocking with his whole body)

1399
00:46:30,401 --> 00:46:31,901
I got a cramp in my leg.

1400
00:46:32,061 --> 00:46:33,730
- It's pointing right at him.
- All right.

1401
00:46:33,731 --> 00:46:34,731
Just throw it.

1402
00:46:34,732 --> 00:46:36,370
(The second member to eat is...)

1403
00:46:36,371 --> 00:46:37,371
Okay!

1404
00:46:37,801 --> 00:46:38,940
- But...
- It's okay.

1405
00:46:38,941 --> 00:46:40,940
Joon did the most chin-ups.

1406
00:46:40,941 --> 00:46:42,070
- Ki Taek, - Just eat as much as you want.

1407
00:46:42,071 --> 00:46:43,280
Since this is a loyalty game,

1408
00:46:43,281 --> 00:46:45,321
- do whatever you want.
- As for this loyalty game,

1409
00:46:45,511 --> 00:46:47,910
it's only right for you to do whatever you want. No pressure.

1410
00:46:47,911 --> 00:46:48,911
Don't feel pressured.

1411
00:46:48,912 --> 00:46:49,950
Don't feel pressured. Just do whatever you want.

1412
00:46:49,951 --> 00:46:52,181
- No pressure at all.
- Just do whatever you want.

1413
00:46:52,381 --> 00:46:53,750
- We won't look.
- Right. We won't look.

1414
00:46:53,751 --> 00:46:55,190
- We won't.
- We won't look. Do as you want.

1415
00:46:55,191 --> 00:46:57,190
- Don't feel pressured.
- But eat just one bite.

1416
00:46:57,191 --> 00:46:58,461
(He feels so pressured.)

1417
00:46:58,561 --> 00:46:59,990
Don't feel pressured. Just do as you want.

1418
00:46:59,991 --> 00:47:01,761
When you're done, give me a tap on the back.

1419
00:47:02,361 --> 00:47:03,400
Do as you want.

1420
00:47:03,401 --> 00:47:04,577
(Ki Taek showed some conscience and ate only a third of it.)

1421
00:47:04,601 --> 00:47:05,601
Just do as you want.

1422
00:47:05,602 --> 00:47:07,731
(I ate as much as my conscience would allow.)

1423
00:47:09,101 --> 00:47:10,570
- Are you guys done?
- Wait. Joon doesn't know...

1424
00:47:10,571 --> 00:47:12,811
- how much you ate.
- That's right.

1425
00:47:13,111 --> 00:47:16,110
My gosh. Ki Taek is really something.

1426
00:47:16,111 --> 00:47:17,317
(He plans to eat it all and put the blame on Ki Taek.)

1427
00:47:17,341 --> 00:47:19,710
Ki Taek, I really had no idea you could do something like this.

1428
00:47:19,711 --> 00:47:20,850
(He's so good at pulling petty tricks.)

1429
00:47:20,851 --> 00:47:22,980
- This isn't enough for us to share.
- Why?

1430
00:47:22,981 --> 00:47:24,881
DinDin, I'm not that kind of a person.

1431
00:47:26,851 --> 00:47:28,720
(DinDin left a measly little piece for Joon.)

1432
00:47:28,721 --> 00:47:30,160
Joon, I only ate this much.

1433
00:47:30,161 --> 00:47:31,290
(And then he pretends he only had a tiny bite.)

1434
00:47:31,291 --> 00:47:32,930
Joon, I only ate this much.

1435
00:47:32,931 --> 00:47:34,690
- I only ate this much.
- Look how stuffed his mouth is.

1436
00:47:34,691 --> 00:47:36,260
- I only ate this much.
- His cheek is bulging out here.

1437
00:47:36,261 --> 00:47:38,031
- I only ate this much.
- Who ate how much?

1438
00:47:38,501 --> 00:47:39,870
Wasn't this really long?

1439
00:47:39,871 --> 00:47:41,000
(He doesn't care who ate the most of it.)

1440
00:47:41,001 --> 00:47:42,730
I can't believe I did 16 chin-ups just to eat this much.

1441
00:47:42,731 --> 00:47:45,601
(I can't believe this is the reward for 16 chin-ups.)

1442
00:47:45,901 --> 00:47:47,370
(Speechless)

1443
00:47:47,371 --> 00:47:48,471
Director Joo,

1444
00:47:48,911 --> 00:47:50,991
are we going to play a game to move to another spot?

1445
00:47:52,241 --> 00:47:54,481
I'm only waiting for that.

1446
00:47:55,781 --> 00:47:57,420
Are you all finished with your food?

1447
00:47:57,421 --> 00:47:59,221
- Yes.
- No, but we'll hear you out.

1448
00:47:59,491 --> 00:48:01,611
- All right, then...
- We'll eat a little more later.

1449
00:48:01,991 --> 00:48:03,390
I'll tell you what you will do next.

1450
00:48:03,391 --> 00:48:05,391
(Team Inhabited Island's next itinerary)

1451
00:48:06,361 --> 00:48:07,390
Now...

1452
00:48:07,391 --> 00:48:08,671
(He gets nervous for no reason.)

1453
00:48:08,831 --> 00:48:11,201
We'll go to our base camp on the deserted island.

1454
00:48:11,731 --> 00:48:12,801
What?

1455
00:48:13,401 --> 00:48:14,570
You got us fooled.

1456
00:48:14,571 --> 00:48:15,931
(What did you just say?)

1457
00:48:16,171 --> 00:48:17,171
What?

1458
00:48:17,172 --> 00:48:20,140
(What are you talking about?)

1459
00:48:20,141 --> 00:48:22,011
- Yes.
- We just came here to eat?

1460
00:48:22,611 --> 00:48:23,880
It's better that we ate some food.

1461
00:48:23,881 --> 00:48:24,881
(Dispirited)

1462
00:48:24,882 --> 00:48:27,511
We showed the base camp in the beginning of the shoot...

1463
00:48:28,151 --> 00:48:29,920
- because we were going back there.
- Really?

1464
00:48:29,921 --> 00:48:30,951
Yes.

1465
00:48:31,981 --> 00:48:35,121
(At the opening this morning)

1466
00:48:35,891 --> 00:48:40,631
(The members headed to the base camp right away.)

1467
00:48:41,231 --> 00:48:46,061
(They entered the island knowing it was the base camp!)

1468
00:48:46,401 --> 00:48:47,971
So, we were all going there in the end.

1469
00:48:48,271 --> 00:48:49,271
That's right.

1470
00:48:49,941 --> 00:48:51,170
That means...

1471
00:48:51,171 --> 00:48:52,400
I'll have spent 16 hours on that island.

1472
00:48:52,401 --> 00:48:53,687
(16 hours except for the brief time he got out)

1473
00:48:53,711 --> 00:48:55,087
- So you just left briefly.
- That's right.

1474
00:48:55,111 --> 00:48:56,941
- He's only out just briefly.
- Exactly.

1475
00:48:57,381 --> 00:48:58,510
You know what's worse?

1476
00:48:58,511 --> 00:49:00,680
It's worse that I got a brief taste of civilization.

1477
00:49:00,681 --> 00:49:01,780
(I've already tasted civilization.)

1478
00:49:01,781 --> 00:49:04,281
It's sad. But still, I'm satisfied.

1479
00:49:04,481 --> 00:49:06,601
At least, I had a hearty meal. There's no food there.

1480
00:49:06,751 --> 00:49:08,190
- That's true.
- Yes.

1481
00:49:08,191 --> 00:49:09,351
Let's get going.

1482
00:49:09,391 --> 00:49:11,890
Let's just take our time and take a duck boat to the island.

1483
00:49:11,891 --> 00:49:13,931
(Darkness has fallen over the sky.)

1484
00:49:14,361 --> 00:49:15,660
(They're heading to the deserted island.)

1485
00:49:15,661 --> 00:49:18,001
I need to go to the bathroom. This is driving me nuts.

1486
00:49:20,271 --> 00:49:22,301
Jong Min has taken so many boats today.

1487
00:49:22,801 --> 00:49:24,601
I went back the forth to that island all day.

1488
00:49:24,641 --> 00:49:25,900
I wish I had stayed in one place.

1489
00:49:25,901 --> 00:49:27,417
(This is the sixth boat he has taken today.)

1490
00:49:27,441 --> 00:49:28,441
It's tiring.

1491
00:49:28,441 --> 00:49:29,441
(Yong Jin is returning to the island in only 3 hours.)

1492
00:49:29,442 --> 00:49:30,710
- Exactly.
- Shooting 2 Days 1 Night is tough.

1493
00:49:30,711 --> 00:49:31,711
It's been a long day.

1494
00:49:32,611 --> 00:49:34,531
I wonder what they're doing after having dinner.

1495
00:49:35,981 --> 00:49:37,220
They must be passing time.

1496
00:49:37,221 --> 00:49:38,281
(Laughing)

1497
00:49:38,681 --> 00:49:40,750
As we're getting closer to the deserted island,

1498
00:49:40,751 --> 00:49:42,120
the air is getting colder.

1499
00:49:42,121 --> 00:49:43,661
- Right.
- It's not unexpected.

1500
00:49:44,091 --> 00:49:45,160
Gosh, it's cold.

1501
00:49:45,161 --> 00:49:46,490
(It's really cold.)

1502
00:49:46,491 --> 00:49:47,661
- Gosh, it's cold.
- Indeed.

1503
00:49:50,531 --> 00:49:52,601
(We're back here in the end.)

1504
00:49:52,731 --> 00:49:53,771
Let's go.

1505
00:49:53,901 --> 00:49:55,871
- Be careful. It's slippery.
- Okay.

1506
00:49:56,231 --> 00:49:57,300
Where is our base camp?

1507
00:49:57,301 --> 00:49:58,600
- Up there.
- Up there?

1508
00:49:58,601 --> 00:50:00,217
(This is my home turf. Just trust me and follow my lead.)

1509
00:50:00,241 --> 00:50:01,241
Is this it?

1510
00:50:01,571 --> 00:50:02,910
- Are there any rooms?
- Of course not.

1511
00:50:02,911 --> 00:50:03,980
(Isn't it obvious?)

1512
00:50:03,981 --> 00:50:05,111
It's an outdoor base camp.

1513
00:50:05,811 --> 00:50:07,350
I guess we'll either sleep outside or in a tent.

1514
00:50:07,351 --> 00:50:08,351
That's right.

1515
00:50:08,352 --> 00:50:09,380
(I guess we'll either sleep outside or in a tent.)

1516
00:50:09,381 --> 00:50:10,450
(Glancing)

1517
00:50:10,451 --> 00:50:11,621
Why do I hear a boat engine?

1518
00:50:12,781 --> 00:50:13,920
What? They're coming.

1519
00:50:13,921 --> 00:50:15,251
- Really?
- Where are they?

1520
00:50:15,821 --> 00:50:16,991
For real?

1521
00:50:17,361 --> 00:50:18,761
Are we all going to sleep here?

1522
00:50:19,321 --> 00:50:20,490
We're here.

1523
00:50:20,491 --> 00:50:22,960
(He feels discouraged somehow.)

1524
00:50:22,961 --> 00:50:24,360
What have you guys been doing?

1525
00:50:24,361 --> 00:50:25,401
Were you eating?

1526
00:50:25,531 --> 00:50:27,100
We were just passing time.

1527
00:50:27,101 --> 00:50:28,201
Really?

1528
00:50:28,471 --> 00:50:29,870
I just passed time.

1529
00:50:29,871 --> 00:50:30,871
What?

1530
00:50:30,872 --> 00:50:32,077
(You guys were passing time just like I did.)

1531
00:50:32,101 --> 00:50:33,341
They ate something. Look here.

1532
00:50:33,911 --> 00:50:35,710
- That's what they ate.
- They ate something.

1533
00:50:35,711 --> 00:50:37,310
