01:13:41,670 --> 01:13:43,410
Isn't it too bright?

2285
01:13:44,410 --> 01:13:46,139
(The lights are on dimly.)

2286
01:13:46,140 --> 01:13:47,279
Can it be this bright?

2287
01:13:47,280 --> 01:13:48,560
- It's too bright, right?
- Yes.

2288
01:13:50,350 --> 01:13:51,430
How do you want the lights?

2289
01:13:52,350 --> 01:13:54,750
But the director isn't here.

2290
01:13:56,890 --> 01:13:58,920
(Yong Jin heads toward the lights.)

2291
01:13:59,090 --> 01:14:01,190
(Yong Jin is here.)

2292
01:14:02,360 --> 01:14:03,360
(He's turning the lights!)

2293
01:14:03,361 --> 01:14:04,390
Like this.

2294
01:14:04,860 --> 01:14:06,090
- That's better.
- Right?

2295
01:14:07,230 --> 01:14:08,230
Nice one.

2296
01:14:08,231 --> 01:14:09,359
(Very satisfied)

2297
01:14:09,360 --> 01:14:10,430
Did you cover the lights?

2298
01:14:10,670 --> 01:14:12,510
- I turned the lights.
- He turned the lights.

2299
01:14:12,800 --> 01:14:14,569
- Is that better?
- Much better.

2300
01:14:14,570 --> 01:14:16,210
- Done, right?
- Nice one.

2301
01:14:17,510 --> 01:14:21,380
(They get ready to sleep with their foil blankets.)

2302
01:14:22,280 --> 01:14:25,780
(They try to sleep while using the sky as their blanket.)

2303
01:14:26,380 --> 01:14:27,380
(Snoring)

2304
01:14:30,450 --> 01:14:34,120
(Team YB is knocked out.)

2305
01:14:34,960 --> 01:14:38,760
(It's warm enough that the sleeping bag isn't needed.)

2306
01:14:39,260 --> 01:14:41,729
(Meanwhile, )

2307
01:14:41,730 --> 01:14:45,830
(the sound of the wind sounds intense outside.)

2308
01:14:46,600 --> 01:14:50,970
(Yong Jin gets startled by the sound.)

2309
01:14:51,670 --> 01:14:53,840
(He tries to fall asleep again.)

2310
01:14:55,880 --> 01:14:58,409
(Flying away)

2311
01:14:58,410 --> 01:15:02,650
(The foil blanket gets blown away by the wind.)

2312
01:15:03,750 --> 01:15:08,959
(Se Yoon's blanket gets blown away as well.)

2313
01:15:08,960 --> 01:15:11,790
(Around 10 minutes pass after his blanket gets blown away.)

2314
01:15:12,860 --> 01:15:15,860
(Searching)

2315
01:15:16,470 --> 01:15:18,330
(Where's my foil blanket?)

2316
01:15:20,170 --> 01:15:22,500
(He carefully gets it back.)

2317
01:15:23,610 --> 01:15:26,979
(They try to endure the sea breeze with the foil blanket.)

2318
01:15:26,980 --> 01:15:30,710
(His blanket ends up tearing up in the end.)

2319
01:15:31,180 --> 01:15:34,350
(The blanket becomes useless because of the wind.)

2320
01:15:35,420 --> 01:15:37,319
(The tough night on the deserted island...)

2321
01:15:37,320 --> 01:15:39,250
(feels endless for Team OB.)

2322
01:15:42,060 --> 01:15:45,759
(After an uncomfortable sleep, )

2323
01:15:45,760 --> 01:15:49,030
(morning comes.)

2324
01:15:55,240 --> 01:15:59,779
(The sea breeze is cold and strong even in the morning.)

2325
01:15:59,780 --> 01:16:01,910
(The foil blanket is all torn up.)

2326
01:16:02,940 --> 01:16:05,480
(Am I the only one who feels cold?)

2327
01:16:08,820 --> 01:16:10,149
Gosh, it's cold.

2328
01:16:10,150 --> 01:16:12,620
(He's forced to wake up because it's cold.)

2329
01:16:13,420 --> 01:16:16,390
(The tent feels warm as it's safe from the wind.)

2330
01:16:16,890 --> 01:16:20,030
(He got rid of the sleeping bag as it's too warm.)

2331
01:16:21,400 --> 01:16:24,970
(The tent makes a big difference.)

2332
01:16:28,600 --> 01:16:31,070
(The wake-up song starts at the right time.)

2333
01:16:32,070 --> 01:16:33,680
(Se Yoon wakes up.)

2334
01:16:34,940 --> 01:16:37,750
(The members in the tent wake up quickly as well.)

2335
01:16:38,580 --> 01:16:40,580
Carefully head to where you got off from the boat.

2336
01:16:41,950 --> 01:16:44,890
(Let's start running.)

2337
01:16:46,720 --> 01:16:48,960
(They set off even though it's hard to open their eyes.)

2338
01:16:50,890 --> 01:16:52,129
I barely managed to survive.

2339
01:16:52,130 --> 01:16:53,330
(It was too cold.)

2340
01:16:53,500 --> 01:16:54,560
Gosh, it's cold.

2341
01:16:54,760 --> 01:16:58,870
(They struggle toward the dock.)

2342
01:17:00,940 --> 01:17:02,300
Did you all sleep well?

2343
01:17:02,740 --> 01:17:03,970
Give us sleeping bags.

2344
01:17:05,010 --> 01:17:07,180
(Was it cold in June?)

2345
01:17:07,280 --> 01:17:09,610
It's the start of June,

2346
01:17:09,750 --> 01:17:11,550
- but it's really cold.
- It was really cold.

2347
01:17:12,510 --> 01:17:13,880
The foil blanket...

2348
01:17:14,650 --> 01:17:16,020
barely kept us alive.

2349
01:17:16,150 --> 01:17:17,550
It wasn't given to us to feel warm.

2350
01:17:17,620 --> 01:17:19,649
Even in the manual,

2351
01:17:19,650 --> 01:17:21,336
it said it was to be used during times of distress.

2352
01:17:21,360 --> 01:17:24,090
It's used to help someone survive.

2353
01:17:24,160 --> 01:17:25,160
Right.

2354
01:17:25,161 --> 01:17:27,099
It makes so much noise...

2355
01:17:27,100 --> 01:17:28,980
- and it gets blown away.
- It gets blown away.

2356
01:17:29,130 --> 01:17:30,569
I was about to go crazy.

2357
01:17:30,570 --> 01:17:31,969
(Sleeping outdoors was too cold in June.)

2358
01:17:31,970 --> 01:17:33,740
It's been a while to feel this way.

2359
01:17:33,800 --> 01:17:35,639
It's nice to see that all of you are safe.

2360
01:17:35,640 --> 01:17:36,640
- Right.
- Right.

2361
01:17:36,641 --> 01:17:39,009
It's time for the morning mission now that all of you are up.

2362
01:17:39,010 --> 01:17:40,110
- Right.
- Sounds good.

2363
01:17:40,380 --> 01:17:41,610
Today's morning mission...

2364
01:17:42,140 --> 01:17:45,350
is The Life-changing Choice, The 2026 Leaving Work Election.

2365
01:17:46,420 --> 01:17:47,649
- The Leaving Work Election?
- Right.

2366
01:17:47,650 --> 01:17:50,620
(The Life-changing Choice, The 2026 Leaving Work Election)

2367
01:17:51,020 --> 01:17:53,920
The member who receives the most number of votes...

2368
01:17:54,360 --> 01:17:56,460
can head home right away after getting on the boat.

2369
01:17:57,190 --> 01:17:58,830
Gosh, this is something new.

2370
01:17:59,360 --> 01:18:02,899
That member can pick another member...

2371
01:18:02,900 --> 01:18:04,429
to be on the boat.

2372
01:18:04,430 --> 01:18:05,999
- The winner?
- Yes.

2373
01:18:06,000 --> 01:18:08,299
- This requires a lot of thinking.
- This is insane!

2374
01:18:08,300 --> 01:18:09,740
A lot of thinking is needed.

2375
01:18:10,310 --> 01:18:11,870
The two who are left until the end...

2376
01:18:12,510 --> 01:18:14,510
will stay with the staff members...

2377
01:18:14,640 --> 01:18:16,780
to clean everything up...

2378
01:18:17,180 --> 01:18:19,050
before taking the last boat.

2379
01:18:19,110 --> 01:18:20,150
Right.

2380
01:18:20,720 --> 01:18:22,580
That's the worst.

2381
01:18:22,950 --> 01:18:24,350
This is insane.

2382
01:18:25,550 --> 01:18:27,590
After ten minutes,

2383
01:18:27,760 --> 01:18:29,960
the first vote will begin.

2384
01:18:31,330 --> 01:18:32,490
(Getting up)

2385
01:18:34,760 --> 01:18:35,929
- Hello.
- Gosh.

2386
01:18:35,930 --> 01:18:36,969
What's up with him?

2387
01:18:36,970 --> 01:18:38,029
(An election campaign suddenly begins.)

2388
01:18:38,030 --> 01:18:39,170
Who are you?

2389
01:18:39,200 --> 01:18:40,300
Hello.

2390
01:18:40,800 --> 01:18:43,100
I'm a candidate in the life-changing election.

2391
01:18:43,710 --> 01:18:45,110
I'm Im Cheol.

2392
01:18:45,410 --> 01:18:46,470
Get out!

2393
01:18:46,980 --> 01:18:48,979
I want to mention this.

2394
01:18:48,980 --> 01:18:50,650
To be honest,

2395
01:18:50,950 --> 01:18:53,150
our shoots have been tough these days.

2396
01:18:53,950 --> 01:18:55,679
- I never felt that way.
- Same here.

2397
01:18:55,680 --> 01:18:57,349
- I enjoyed the shoots so much.
- I enjoyed them as well.

2398
01:18:57,350 --> 01:18:58,866
- It must've been tough for him.
- Right.

2399
01:18:58,890 --> 01:19:01,010
He can't block the sunlight for us as he's too short.

2400
01:19:02,120 --> 01:19:03,160
Cover the sunlight for us.

2401
01:19:03,490 --> 01:19:05,529
If there's anything I can do for all of you...

2402
01:19:05,530 --> 01:19:06,760
Nice.

2403
01:19:06,900 --> 01:19:08,830
If there's anything I can do for all of you,

2404
01:19:09,130 --> 01:19:10,229
I will do my best...

2405
01:19:10,230 --> 01:19:11,700
- to cover the sunlight.
- Nice.

2406
01:19:11,970 --> 01:19:14,640
For all of you,

2407
01:19:15,100 --> 01:19:16,770
I will be your fall guy.

2408
01:19:17,040 --> 01:19:18,910
I'll do the things you can't do.

2409
01:19:19,270 --> 01:19:21,809
I'll cause a fuss and do my best...

2410
01:19:21,810 --> 01:19:23,810
to secure a better filming environment!

2411
01:19:24,010 --> 01:19:27,950
(I will be your fall guy. Number 1: Im Cheol)

2412
01:19:28,220 --> 01:19:29,749
Please remember Im Cheol!

2413
01:19:29,750 --> 01:19:31,720
I will be your worker!

2414
01:19:31,850 --> 01:19:33,289
DinDin is DinDin!

2415
01:19:33,290 --> 01:19:34,690
- How boring.
- DinDin!

2416
01:19:35,060 --> 01:19:37,290
He always sings that song for every election.

2417
01:19:37,830 --> 01:19:40,360
It has to be Lee Yong Jin no matter what

2418
01:19:40,760 --> 01:19:42,299
- Are you number two?
- Yes.

2419
01:19:42,300 --> 01:19:44,870
- Number two.
- Yes. I won't say much.

2420
01:19:45,070 --> 01:19:47,570
(It has to be Lee Yong Jin. Number 2, Lee Yong Jin)

2421
01:19:47,940 --> 01:19:49,669
If I got...

2422
01:19:49,670 --> 01:19:52,039
- It's a Q and A session.
- to leave first...

2423
01:19:52,040 --> 01:19:53,516
- Who would you bring with you?
- Who would you bring?

2424
01:19:53,540 --> 01:19:54,680
It's one of three.

2425
01:19:55,010 --> 01:19:56,709
Jong Min, Se Yoon, or Ki Taek.

2426
01:19:56,710 --> 01:19:58,079
You're trying to be smart with us.

2427
01:19:58,080 --> 01:19:59,440
Are you trying to get three votes?

2428
01:19:59,920 --> 01:20:01,580
You have to choose one.

2429
01:20:01,780 --> 01:20:03,889
- Just pick one person.
- Pick just one of them.

2430
01:20:03,890 --> 01:20:05,296
(The voters won't let him get away with it.)

2431
01:20:05,320 --> 01:20:06,350
(Sighing)

2432
01:20:07,690 --> 01:20:08,690
What's with that sigh?

2433
01:20:08,790 --> 01:20:11,089
- Right.
- Your approval rating is dropping.

2434
01:20:11,090 --> 01:20:12,190
I'll be honest.

2435
01:20:13,130 --> 01:20:14,360
I won't choose anyone.

2436
01:20:14,630 --> 01:20:15,959
I'll let the three of them play rock-paper-scissors.

2437
01:20:15,960 --> 01:20:16,969
(He will decide it with a game of rock-paper-scissors.)

2438
01:20:16,970 --> 01:20:18,829
- That's not bad.
- You'll do rock-paper-scissors.

2439
01:20:18,830 --> 01:20:20,039
It's not bad.

2440
01:20:20,040 --> 01:20:21,976
- It's a matter of luck.
- They'll do rock-paper-scissors.

2441
01:20:22,000 --> 01:20:23,740
Okay. Is there Candidate Number Three?

2442
01:20:24,010 --> 01:20:25,340
I'm Number Three.

2443
01:20:25,570 --> 01:20:27,380
- No, you're Number Four.
- Is that so?

2444
01:20:27,480 --> 01:20:28,539
Wait a little more.

2445
01:20:28,540 --> 01:20:30,050
(They're so funny.)

2446
01:20:30,110 --> 01:20:31,680
Which party are you with?

2447
01:20:32,150 --> 01:20:33,210
The Fool Party.

2448
01:20:34,480 --> 01:20:35,780
That's catchy.

2449
01:20:36,480 --> 01:20:37,990
I belong to the Fool Party!

2450
01:20:38,950 --> 01:20:41,590
I'm a fool who knows nothing but you.

2451
01:20:42,190 --> 01:20:45,660
(A fool who only cares about you. Number 3, Kim Jong Min)

2452
01:20:45,760 --> 01:20:47,460
- I'm a newlywed.
- What?

2453
01:20:47,800 --> 01:20:49,630
My wife is waiting for me at home.

2454
01:20:50,700 --> 01:20:52,130
I have to go home early.

2455
01:20:52,170 --> 01:20:54,699
My wife and child are waiting for me as well.

2456
01:20:54,700 --> 01:20:57,940
My mother-in-law came all the way from Busan and is waiting for me.

2457
01:20:58,170 --> 01:20:59,739
Is that why you want to go home late?

2458
01:20:59,740 --> 01:21:01,179
I need to go see my mother-in-law.

2459
01:21:01,180 --> 01:21:04,080
But when she heard that I'd be shooting 2 Days 1 Night,

2460
01:21:04,210 --> 01:21:06,509
she told me, "Don't worry about me and take your time."

2461
01:21:06,510 --> 01:21:08,649
That's what I heard before I left.

2462
01:21:08,650 --> 01:21:10,089
Then you don't have to go home early.

2463
01:21:10,090 --> 01:21:11,120
That's not true.

2464
01:21:11,390 --> 01:21:15,260
Hello. I'm Number Four Moon Se Yoon.

2465
01:21:16,390 --> 01:21:19,130
I'm going out on a fishing boat

2466
01:21:20,030 --> 01:21:21,306
I have an important announcement to make.

2467
01:21:21,330 --> 01:21:23,370
I will not be leaving through this mission.

2468
01:21:24,100 --> 01:21:25,269
(He won't leave?)

2469
01:21:25,270 --> 01:21:27,340
I'm very disappointed in you guys.

2470
01:21:27,770 --> 01:21:29,239
Why do you all try so hard to leave early?

2471
01:21:29,240 --> 01:21:30,509
And you always complain...

2472
01:21:30,510 --> 01:21:32,016
about being tired and having a backache.

2473
01:21:32,040 --> 01:21:34,739
I absolutely love being in this place...

2474
01:21:34,740 --> 01:21:35,780
with the production crew.

2475
01:21:36,340 --> 01:21:38,049
- So, to me, - So?

2476
01:21:38,050 --> 01:21:40,250
This is a paradise.

2477
01:21:40,580 --> 01:21:44,750
(This is a paradise. Number 4, Moon Se Yoon)

2478
01:21:44,820 --> 01:21:46,919
Even my mother-in-law is...

2479
01:21:46,920 --> 01:21:49,259
a big fan of 2 Days 1 Night.

2480
01:21:49,260 --> 01:21:51,759
She told me to come home late and just focus on being funny.

2481
01:21:51,760 --> 01:21:53,700
- That's my...
- This is a bad move.

2482
01:21:53,830 --> 01:21:55,130
This is what she said. So I...

2483
01:21:55,600 --> 01:21:58,000
- You won't go home?
- I have a candidate that I support.

2484
01:21:59,200 --> 01:22:01,400
(Stirred up)

2485
01:22:01,540 --> 01:22:02,569
What?

2486
01:22:02,570 --> 01:22:04,139
(Surprised)

2487
01:22:04,140 --> 01:22:06,640
- I'm okay.
- You can't form a coalition here.

2488
01:22:06,910 --> 01:22:08,079
Is it okay to announce a pledge...

2489
01:22:08,080 --> 01:22:09,239
and merge candidacies at the same time?

2490
01:22:09,240 --> 01:22:10,586
(Merging candidacies the moment pledges are rolled out)

2491
01:22:10,610 --> 01:22:11,649
- I...
- He announces unification...

2492
01:22:11,650 --> 01:22:13,996
- while rolling out his pledges.
- I'll make an announcement here.

2493
01:22:14,020 --> 01:22:16,889
I want to support this candidate.

2494
01:22:16,890 --> 01:22:17,919
- I...
- Who?

2495
01:22:17,920 --> 01:22:20,119
Support Candidate Lee Yong Jin.

2496
01:22:20,120 --> 01:22:21,459
- What?
- Why are you holding my hand?

2497
01:22:21,460 --> 01:22:24,230
- It has to be Lee Yong Jin - It has to be Lee Yong Jin

2498
01:22:24,660 --> 01:22:27,360
- It has to be Lee Yong Jin - Thank you.

2499
01:22:27,900 --> 01:22:30,029
I don't think I achieved all this on my own.

2500
01:22:30,030 --> 01:22:31,229
- No.
- Thank you.

2501
01:22:31,230 --> 01:22:34,340
(Lee Yong Jin and Moon Se Yoon agree to join forces.)

2502
01:22:34,770 --> 01:22:37,510
We have two candidates left.

2503
01:22:37,870 --> 01:22:39,169
- The Challenge Party?
- Hello.

2504
01:22:39,170 --> 01:22:40,530
I'm Lee Joon from the Catch Party.

2505
01:22:41,180 --> 01:22:43,450
You should think carefully about this.

2506
01:22:46,110 --> 01:22:47,180
Think about what?

2507
01:22:47,920 --> 01:22:48,950
You have to withdraw!

2508
01:22:51,050 --> 01:22:52,850
You have to pull out for saying such a thing.

2509
01:22:55,820 --> 01:22:59,490
(Number 5, Lee Joon)

2510
01:22:59,960 --> 01:23:00,960
I...

2511
01:23:00,961 --> 01:23:01,999
(Candidate 6, Lee Ki Taek)

2512
01:23:02,000 --> 01:23:03,770
I want to be chosen...

2513
01:23:04,270 --> 01:23:05,570
to get off work.

2514
01:23:06,500 --> 01:23:08,970
I'll tell you the candidate I support.

2515
01:23:09,040 --> 01:23:11,139
- Right away?
- A candidate...

2516
01:23:11,140 --> 01:23:12,410
supported by Lee Ki Taek?

2517
01:23:12,840 --> 01:23:14,140
I support...

2518
01:23:15,010 --> 01:23:17,049
(Who would it be?)

2519
01:23:17,050 --> 01:23:18,350
Candidate Lee Yong Jin.

2520
01:23:18,450 --> 01:23:20,350
- What?
- I'll stake my destiny on him.

2521
01:23:20,580 --> 01:23:22,179
- They will leave together.
- So, you two are in cahoots...

2522
01:23:22,180 --> 01:23:23,819
to leave together?

2523
01:23:23,820 --> 01:23:26,120
Se Yoon said he'd stay.

2524
01:23:26,750 --> 01:23:27,819
(This isn't what I planned.)

2525
01:23:27,820 --> 01:23:30,330
So I'll vote for Yong Jin.

2526
01:23:30,590 --> 01:23:31,659
Wait.

2527
01:23:31,660 --> 01:23:34,360
(Wait.)

2528
01:23:35,030 --> 01:23:36,459
- All right. Se Yoon.
- Are you leaving the party?

2529
01:23:36,460 --> 01:23:38,570
What's going through your mind right now?

2530
01:23:38,700 --> 01:23:41,500
I just mentioned that I support...

2531
01:23:42,270 --> 01:23:43,740
Candidate Lee Yong Jin,

2532
01:23:43,970 --> 01:23:46,740
but as he joined forces with Candidate Lee Ki Taek,

2533
01:23:46,840 --> 01:23:48,239
my position has become pathetic.

2534
01:23:48,240 --> 01:23:50,249
Thanks to Candidate Lee Ki Taek, who is trying to push me out...

2535
01:23:50,250 --> 01:23:51,549
and expand his power,

2536
01:23:51,550 --> 01:23:54,750
I've ended up endorsing another candidate here.

2537
01:23:55,220 --> 01:23:58,120
I am withdrawing my support for Candidate Lee Yong Jin,

2538
01:23:58,450 --> 01:24:00,190
and instead,

2539
01:24:00,990 --> 01:24:03,160
I will support a candidate...

2540
01:24:03,690 --> 01:24:05,629
who will be helpful to our show.

2541
01:24:05,630 --> 01:24:07,460
The candidate I support, trust,

2542
01:24:07,660 --> 01:24:10,030
- and believe in is...
- Welcome back.

2543
01:24:10,230 --> 01:24:11,400
Lee Joon.

2544
01:24:13,200 --> 01:24:14,240
What?

2545
01:24:14,340 --> 01:24:15,340
(Candidate Se Yoon declares support for Lee Joon.)

2546
01:24:15,341 --> 01:24:17,169
- It's 50-50.
- Our best friend.

2547
01:24:17,170 --> 01:24:20,540
- Lee Joon!
- Lee Joon!

2548
01:24:20,780 --> 01:24:22,780
It's Lee Joon

2549
01:24:22,840 --> 01:24:24,850
- It's Lee Joon - It's Lee Joon

2550
01:24:24,980 --> 01:24:26,579
(The completely tangled and unpredictable election)

2551
01:24:26,580 --> 01:24:28,850
This is difficult. It's all twisted.

2552
01:24:29,020 --> 01:24:30,079
Think carefully.

2553
01:24:30,080 --> 01:24:32,150
- He is...
- If I get elected,

2554
01:24:32,820 --> 01:24:34,319
who do you think I will bring?

2555
01:24:34,320 --> 01:24:35,919
- Will you bring me? Are you sure?
- Yes.

2556
01:24:35,920 --> 01:24:36,929
Promise me.

2557
01:24:36,930 --> 01:24:38,029
(DinDin wins over Ki Taek who announced to support Yong Jin.)

2558
01:24:38,030 --> 01:24:39,360
Will you bring me, not Joon?

2559
01:24:40,130 --> 01:24:42,560
(Don't tell Yong Jin.)

2560
01:24:42,860 --> 01:24:46,599
(DinDin and Ki Taek formed a secret alliance before the vote.)

2561
01:24:46,600 --> 01:24:48,299
Please support me, guys.

2562
01:24:48,300 --> 01:24:49,739
(The 1st getting-off-work vote commences.)

2563
01:24:49,740 --> 01:24:51,170
I'll appreciate your support.

2564
01:24:55,010 --> 01:24:57,209
(A choice that changes your life)

2565
01:24:57,210 --> 01:24:59,910
(Who will get off work, and who will be left behind?)

2566
01:25:01,050 --> 01:25:02,619
What kind of plot twist awaits us?

2567
01:25:02,620 --> 01:25:03,720
(The voting has closed.)

2568
01:25:05,250 --> 01:25:08,160
(The counting begins with DinDin.)

2569
01:25:08,560 --> 01:25:12,190
(As expected, DinDin voted for himself.)

2570
01:25:13,430 --> 01:25:14,929
(The second ballot to be opened is Lee Ki Taek.)

2571
01:25:14,930 --> 01:25:15,960
I...

2572
01:25:17,000 --> 01:25:19,500
I'm sure Ki Taek voted for Yong Jin.

2573
01:25:19,770 --> 01:25:22,299
(Is it Yong Jin whom he endorsed?)

2574
01:25:22,300 --> 01:25:24,610
(Or is it DinDin, with whom he made a secret alliance?)

2575
01:25:24,940 --> 01:25:26,980
(What is the result?)

2576
01:25:27,640 --> 01:25:28,839
I kept my promise.

2577
01:25:28,840 --> 01:25:30,426
(Ki Taek kept his promise on the secret alliance.)

2578
01:25:30,450 --> 01:25:32,579
I kept my promise.

2579
01:25:32,580 --> 01:25:33,820
(You voted for me, right? Yes.)

2580
01:25:34,580 --> 01:25:37,090
(DinDin, 2 votes)

2581
01:25:38,350 --> 01:25:39,820
I kept my promise.

2582
01:25:39,890 --> 01:25:40,890
(I trust you.)

2583
01:25:41,860 --> 01:25:44,089
(Yong Jin believes they're in the same boat.)

2584
01:25:44,090 --> 01:25:45,160
I believe...

2585
01:25:45,360 --> 01:25:48,830
this person played the most crucial role this week.

2586
01:25:49,260 --> 01:25:51,800
(Lee Yong Jin, 1 vote)

2587
01:25:53,170 --> 01:25:55,700
I think this candidate really stepped up and shone.

2588
01:25:56,170 --> 01:25:57,309
He should leave early.

2589
01:25:57,310 --> 01:25:59,640
(They both voted for themselves.)

2590
01:26:00,040 --> 01:26:03,479
(Current ballot counting status)

2591
01:26:03,480 --> 01:26:06,650
(Only Se Yoon's ballot remains.)

2592
01:26:07,950 --> 01:26:11,790
(DinDin is in the lead with 2 votes.)

2593
01:26:13,050 --> 01:26:15,519
(Will DinDin be elected like this? What's Se Yoon's choice?)

2594
01:26:15,520 --> 01:26:17,360
All right. The last ballot.

2595
01:26:17,460 --> 01:26:19,460
(Lee Joon)

2596
01:26:19,630 --> 01:26:20,630
(Lee Joon, 2 votes)

2597
01:26:20,631 --> 01:26:21,660
What?

2598
01:26:21,930 --> 01:26:23,670
Since it's a tie,

2599
01:26:23,930 --> 01:26:25,170
we will hold a revote.

2600
01:26:25,230 --> 01:26:26,270
Everyone.

2601
01:26:26,470 --> 01:26:29,000
Who was the one who helped you when things were tough?

2602
01:26:29,270 --> 01:26:30,610
I'm so disappointed.

2603
01:26:30,870 --> 01:26:33,169
He's serious. He's disappointed for real.

2604
01:26:33,170 --> 01:26:34,840
Let's just get this over with and leave.

2605
01:26:35,780 --> 01:26:37,080
I need to go to the bathroom.

2606
01:26:37,150 --> 01:26:40,179
All right. We have DinDin and Lee Joon.

2607
01:26:40,180 --> 01:26:42,449
You are to raise your hand only once.

2608
01:26:42,450 --> 01:26:43,450
- Okay.
- All right.

2609
01:26:44,650 --> 01:26:47,119
Please raise your hand if you are voting for DinDin.

2610
01:26:47,120 --> 01:26:49,000
(Raise your hand if you are voting for DinDin.)

2611
01:26:49,260 --> 01:26:50,889
(1 vote from Ki Taek for the secret alliance)

2612
01:26:50,890 --> 01:26:52,059
How many votes would it be?

2613
01:26:52,060 --> 01:26:53,329
I have a bad feeling about this.

2614
01:26:53,330 --> 01:26:54,360
(Nervous)

2615
01:26:55,360 --> 01:26:57,130
(Not a single hand is raised.)

2616
01:26:57,270 --> 01:26:59,100
- Is that it?
- Move on right away.

2617
01:26:59,270 --> 01:27:01,799
All right. Those who vote for Joon.

2618
01:27:01,800 --> 01:27:03,300
- Raise your hand.
- It's over.

2619
01:27:03,500 --> 01:27:04,540
You should go, Joon.

2620
01:27:04,710 --> 01:27:06,539
- Lee Joon gets off work.
- I can't believe this.

2621
01:27:06,540 --> 01:27:07,540
You should go.

2622
01:27:07,541 --> 01:27:09,509
- I supported you.
- Yes!

2623
01:27:09,510 --> 01:27:10,680
Candidate Lee Joon!

2624
01:27:11,110 --> 01:27:13,049
(A deep bow of gratitude)

2625
01:27:13,050 --> 01:27:15,819
- Lee Joon!
- Lee Joon!

2626
01:27:15,820 --> 01:27:18,290
- It has to be Lee Joon - It has to be Lee Joon

2627
01:27:18,450 --> 01:27:20,420
Joon, the boat is coming.

2628
01:27:20,990 --> 01:27:22,619
- Who will you board the boat with?
- It's approaching.

2629
01:27:22,620 --> 01:27:24,229
It's time to announce.

2630
01:27:24,230 --> 01:27:26,089
I have two people in mind,

2631
01:27:26,090 --> 01:27:27,929
- but I don't know whom to choose.
- We won't be upset.

2632
01:27:27,930 --> 01:27:29,059
We won't sulk.

2633
01:27:29,060 --> 01:27:30,369
- This is driving me crazy.
- Then...

2634
01:27:30,370 --> 01:27:31,890
- Please announce your choice.
- Good.

2635
01:27:32,070 --> 01:27:34,200
- Go ahead.
- What's Lee Joon's choice?

2636
01:27:34,270 --> 01:27:36,146
(Which supporter will get to leave with Lee Joon?)

2637
01:27:36,170 --> 01:27:39,339
One, two, three.

2638
01:27:39,340 --> 01:27:40,539
What is Lee Joon's choice?

2639
01:27:40,540 --> 01:27:41,580
Moon Se Yoon!

2640
01:27:41,940 --> 01:27:42,980
Are you serious?

2641
01:27:44,350 --> 01:27:45,350
Thank you.

2642
01:27:45,351 --> 01:27:47,420
Jong Min, what are you doing? Grab him.

2643
01:27:47,850 --> 01:27:49,579
- Come here.
- What?

2644
01:27:49,580 --> 01:27:51,220
- Teach him a lesson.
- Hey.

2645
01:27:51,390 --> 01:27:52,989
The boat is here.

2646
01:27:52,990 --> 01:27:54,559
Pack your stuff and go.

2647
01:27:54,560 --> 01:27:56,089
- I'm sorry.
- Get your stuff.

2648
01:27:56,090 --> 01:27:57,630
- You?
- This is meaningless.

2649
01:27:58,330 --> 01:28:00,830
(I want to leave the deserted island.)

2650
01:28:01,560 --> 01:28:03,500
- Bye.
- We'll get going.

2651
01:28:05,030 --> 01:28:07,030
(Jealous)

2652
01:28:07,500 --> 01:28:08,570
Gosh, it's hot.

2653
01:28:09,470 --> 01:28:10,570
I told you...

2654
01:28:10,840 --> 01:28:12,839
that the voting takes place every 30 minutes.

2655
01:28:12,840 --> 01:28:14,580
- Yes.
- What are we doing for 30 minutes?

2656
01:28:14,880 --> 01:28:17,180
Isn't it obvious? We'll be just killing time.

2657
01:28:19,510 --> 01:28:22,380
We will proceed with the next voting soon.

2658
01:28:23,120 --> 01:28:25,720
(Feeling happy on their way home)

2659
01:28:26,020 --> 01:28:27,119
Thank you.

2660
01:28:27,120 --> 01:28:29,020
My pleasure. Thank you.

2661
01:28:29,420 --> 01:28:31,030
This is the best day ever.

2662
01:28:31,390 --> 01:28:33,560
- I want to go there.
- We're leaving so early.

2663
01:28:33,900 --> 01:28:35,620
I wish I could travel to a place like that.

2664
01:28:36,260 --> 01:28:38,530
I bet there will be a huge difference.

2665
01:28:38,870 --> 01:28:41,240
It takes a long time to vote.

2666
01:28:42,340 --> 01:28:44,240
Things will get ugly for those who are left.

2667
01:28:44,470 --> 01:28:46,409
Seriously, it will be ugly.

2668
01:28:46,410 --> 01:28:48,250
(Things will get ugly for those who are left.)

2669
01:28:48,410 --> 01:28:51,980
(They are waiting before things get ugly.)

2670
01:28:53,410 --> 01:28:54,880
I'm nervous. I have a bad feeling.

2671
01:28:58,920 --> 01:29:01,890
Everyone. Two of you will be leaving this time.

2672
01:29:02,460 --> 01:29:03,960
And the other two...

2673
01:29:04,130 --> 01:29:06,960
will clean up after the shoot.

2674
01:29:07,090 --> 01:29:08,159
So it will take a while.

2675
01:29:08,160 --> 01:29:09,960
This is going to be a crucial vote.

2676
01:29:12,430 --> 01:29:17,170
(A tense 30-minute wait at the dock before the storm)

2677
01:29:17,510 --> 01:29:18,809
All right. Write down the name.

2678
01:29:18,810 --> 01:29:20,880
(30 minutes later, the 2nd vote commences.)

2679
01:29:21,510 --> 01:29:22,680
(Glancing)

2680
01:29:23,780 --> 01:29:28,650
(Who will be chosen to get off work?)

2681
01:29:28,980 --> 01:29:30,990
(The vote has closed.)

2682
01:29:31,190 --> 01:29:32,489
Were the results divided?

2683
01:29:32,490 --> 01:29:35,289
We have a winner here.

2684
01:29:35,290 --> 01:29:36,560
(The winner has been decided.)

2685
01:29:36,820 --> 01:29:38,190
We have a winner.

2686
01:29:38,560 --> 01:29:39,960
- Thanks in advance.
- Sure.

2687
01:29:40,630 --> 01:29:42,030
I won't forget what you did for me.

2688
01:29:42,730 --> 01:29:44,730
Okay. Here's the first vote.

2689
01:29:45,570 --> 01:29:47,030
- DinDin.
- Thanks.

2690
01:29:47,070 --> 01:29:48,999
Who voted for me? Thank you.

2691
01:29:49,000 --> 01:29:50,640
- I did.
- Thanks.

2692
01:29:51,470 --> 01:29:52,710
It's 100-percent you.

2693
01:29:53,110 --> 01:29:54,110
Here goes.

2694
01:29:54,110 --> 01:29:55,110
(Will DinDin win?)

2695
01:29:55,510 --> 01:29:57,309
(Who gets the second vote?)

2696
01:29:57,310 --> 01:29:58,310
Lee Ki Taek.

2697
01:30:01,880 --> 01:30:04,190
- Look at him.
- No. It wasn't me.

2698
01:30:04,790 --> 01:30:05,790
Thank you.

2699
01:30:05,791 --> 01:30:07,020
(Thanks anyway.)

2700
01:30:07,120 --> 01:30:09,290
(Who voted for Ki Taek?)

2701
01:30:09,860 --> 01:30:10,930
The next one.

2702
01:30:11,460 --> 01:30:12,489
Lee Yong Jin.

2703
01:30:12,490 --> 01:30:13,759
(The third vote went to Yong Jin.)

2704
01:30:13,760 --> 01:30:14,830
Hang on.

2705
01:30:15,360 --> 01:30:18,130
It's down to the last vote.

2706
01:30:18,400 --> 01:30:19,570
It looks like...

2707
01:30:19,870 --> 01:30:21,299
the result is crystal clear.

2708
01:30:21,300 --> 01:30:22,700
(He's sure he'll win the vote.)

2709
01:30:22,940 --> 01:30:25,970
This is the fourth and final vote.

2710
01:30:26,370 --> 01:30:28,040
It's the last one.

2711
01:30:29,740 --> 01:30:30,809
(Will DinDin win...)

2712
01:30:30,810 --> 01:30:33,449
The next person to go home is...

2713
01:30:33,450 --> 01:30:34,820
(as expected?)

2714
01:30:36,480 --> 01:30:37,519
Lee Ki Taek.

2715
01:30:37,520 --> 01:30:41,019
(Lee Ki Taek)

2716
01:30:41,020 --> 01:30:42,120
What did I say?

2717
01:30:45,390 --> 01:30:47,929
(It's not me?)

2718
01:30:47,930 --> 01:30:49,959
What just happened?

2719
01:30:49,960 --> 01:30:51,030
(What happened?)

2720
01:30:51,370 --> 01:30:55,269
(How Ki Taek ruined the alliance)

2721
01:30:55,270 --> 01:30:57,099
- Okay.
- We'll get our stuff.

2722
01:30:57,100 --> 01:30:58,569
(30 minutes ago, Jong Min, Yong Jin, Ki Taek got their stuff.)

2723
01:30:58,570 --> 01:31:00,980
I'm off to get my belongings.

2724
01:31:02,210 --> 01:31:04,680
Ki Taek. Switch things around.

2725
01:31:05,310 --> 01:31:06,950
Let's go home.

2726
01:31:07,050 --> 01:31:09,019
- Let's give Ki Taek a chance.
- We'll see.

2727
01:31:09,020 --> 01:31:10,519
Yes. Jong Min.

2728
01:31:10,520 --> 01:31:13,220
It's the only way to make Ki Taek not choose DinDin.

2729
01:31:13,420 --> 01:31:15,020
- Ki Taek. I'll vote for you.
- Okay.

2730
01:31:15,190 --> 01:31:16,860
- Seriously. Vote for yourself.
- Okay.

2731
01:31:17,220 --> 01:31:18,530
We must win with smarts.

2732
01:31:18,760 --> 01:31:20,389
What just happened?

2733
01:31:20,390 --> 01:31:22,229
(DinDin is still confused.)

2734
01:31:22,230 --> 01:31:24,670
- Thank you.
- Ki Taek.

2735
01:31:25,730 --> 01:31:28,070
- You know, right?
- Yes, I know.

2736
01:31:28,740 --> 01:31:31,340
(You know I voted for you, right?)

2737
01:31:31,540 --> 01:31:32,540
Ki Taek.

2738
01:31:32,541 --> 01:31:33,980
(There's me too, Ki Taek.)

2739
01:31:34,180 --> 01:31:37,280
The person I'll leave the deserted island with is...

2740
01:31:38,680 --> 01:31:40,180
- Lee Yong Jin!
- Yes!

2741
01:31:40,780 --> 01:31:41,780
Yes!

2742
01:31:43,350 --> 01:31:45,719
From now on, you, honestly...

2743
01:31:45,720 --> 01:31:47,200
I won't hang out with you ever again.

2744
01:31:47,590 --> 01:31:49,819
You... From now on...

2745
01:31:49,820 --> 01:31:51,089
- It's over.
- Sorry.

2746
01:31:51,090 --> 01:31:52,090
(You betrayed me?)

2747
01:31:52,360 --> 01:31:53,760
How could you?

2748
01:31:54,000 --> 01:31:55,000
Let's go.

2749
01:31:55,230 --> 01:31:57,570
- See?
- I voted for you so far.

2750
01:31:57,770 --> 01:31:59,570
- See? You failed.
- You know, right?

2751
01:32:00,570 --> 01:32:02,300
I got played again.

2752
01:32:02,540 --> 01:32:04,409
The boat will be here soon.

2753
01:32:04,410 --> 01:32:05,870
It's here.

2754
01:32:07,110 --> 01:32:10,340
The next to go home are Yong Jin and Ki Taek.

2755
01:32:10,650 --> 01:32:12,679
- You can go home.
- Thanks. Good job, everyone.

2756
01:32:12,680 --> 01:32:14,450
- Bye.
- See you.

2757
01:32:14,920 --> 01:32:16,819
Good job, production team.

2758
01:32:16,820 --> 01:32:18,350
(Yong Jin and Ki Taek go home.)

2759
01:32:20,390 --> 01:32:21,959
- Rest up.
- Okay.

2760
01:32:21,960 --> 01:32:23,659
Put your stuff down and wear the vest.

2761
01:32:23,660 --> 01:32:25,380
(They get on the boat to leave the island.)

2762
01:32:25,660 --> 01:32:27,459
- It went well.
- However fast they move,

2763
01:32:27,460 --> 01:32:29,630
it'll take an hour and a half to pack up and leave.

2764
01:32:30,360 --> 01:32:32,770
Joon and DinDin can't be trusted.

2765
01:32:34,240 --> 01:32:35,670
You must trust me.

2766
01:32:35,900 --> 01:32:36,999
We joined together.

2767
01:32:37,000 --> 01:32:39,639
- Yes. I saw that today.
- Didn't you?

2768
01:32:39,640 --> 01:32:41,360
(They form an alliance on the return trip.)

2769
01:32:42,980 --> 01:32:45,279
You fold and I'll pack.

2770
01:32:45,280 --> 01:32:49,879
(The last two work hard to help pack up.)

2771
01:32:49,880 --> 01:32:50,890
What is this?

2772
01:32:51,520 --> 01:32:55,090
Why am I so jealous that they got to leave a few hours ahead?

2773
01:32:55,760 --> 01:32:57,089
- Seriously.
- Right?

2774
01:32:57,090 --> 01:32:58,830
- It's nothing, really.
- One hour...

2775
01:33:01,300 --> 01:33:02,929
(Talking only slows you down.)

2776
01:33:02,930 --> 01:33:04,130
Gosh.

2777
01:33:05,670 --> 01:33:08,440
(They cleaned up for 1 hour and 30 minutes.)

2778
01:33:08,500 --> 01:33:10,040
It's nice and clean. Let's go.

2779
01:33:10,670 --> 01:33:12,010
- It's here.
- It's here!

2780
01:33:12,440 --> 01:33:13,510
Over here!

2781
01:33:15,610 --> 01:33:18,079
Help!

2782
01:33:18,080 --> 01:33:22,679
(They left the island 3 hours after the 1st team left.)

2783
01:33:22,680 --> 01:33:27,720
(Jong Min and DinDin leave last.)

2784
01:33:27,790 --> 01:33:29,719
(Next episode)

2785
01:33:29,720 --> 01:33:31,260
(Travel along Route 7)

2786
01:33:32,130 --> 01:33:33,789
(The backbone of Korea...)

2787
01:33:33,790 --> 01:33:35,159
(that goes along the east coast)

2788
01:33:35,160 --> 01:33:36,800
(We follow the national highway...)

2789
01:33:37,430 --> 01:33:39,400
(on a healing trip along Route 7.)

2790
01:33:39,530 --> 01:33:42,299
(They eat.)

2791
01:33:42,300 --> 01:33:44,770
(They have fun.)

2792
01:33:45,540 --> 01:33:49,239
(They have some good times.)

2793
01:33:49,240 --> 01:33:50,540
(The happiness doesn't last.)

2794
01:33:51,410 --> 01:33:53,210
